Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.46,0:28:51.05,Default,,0,0,0,,After billions and billions of years, the earth has become, it has become very, very,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.05,0:28:56.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and billions of years, a crust, the surface was cool enough for a crust to form.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.58,0:29:01.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The center of the earth is still molten, still molten lava.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.67,0:29:05.69,Default,,0,0,0,,But the crust cooled off, the possibilities, you see,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.69,0:29:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,because potentiality only becomes actuality when conditions prevail.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.25,0:29:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So you had to have a crust on this earth for life to be able to survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.75,0:29:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Life evolved then.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.15,0:29:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The first signs of life as algae, viruses.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.11,0:29:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Viruses are not conscious.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.16,0:29:27.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Algae are not conscious.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.05,0:29:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Chlorophyll, living via chlorophyll, they're not conscious.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.40,0:29:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The virus replicates its DNA, but it's not conscious.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.08,0:29:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.39,0:29:43.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't experience that it exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.29,0:29:48.79,Default,,0,0,0,,However, it doesn't need anything anyway because it's provided.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.64,0:29:52.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Chlorophyll, if you go all green, we could just sit in the sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.35,0:29:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Get all the energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.33,0:29:55.11,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't have to eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.33,0:29:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't have to eat, you don't have to work.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.85,0:29:57.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.39,0:30:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a brick that'd be colored green.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.57,0:30:09.34,Default,,0,0,0,,For animal life, bacteria is the first conscious being, calibrates as one.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.19,0:30:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And what is the characteristic of life?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.95,0:30:15.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is the secret of the ego, and I'll get you off guilt about it forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.43,0:30:20.91,Default,,0,0,0,,In order for life to survive, it's got to be self-serving.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.32,0:30:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.82,0:30:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it's not born with energy or a source of energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.50,0:30:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It can only survive by getting energy out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.73,0:30:35.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The amoeba has to encompass something else in order to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.26,0:30:37.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The bacteria has to get something.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.00,0:30:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The core of the ego is, its message is, in order to survive, you have to get.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.07,0:30:46.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The intellect then expands that.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.64,0:30:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The more you get, the better.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.29,0:30:52.43,Default,,0,0,0,,The squirrel has that idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.35,0:30:56.33,Default,,0,0,0,,One time I had a whole thing of things, and I put them on the lawn,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.98,0:31:00.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and I went crazy, running and digging a hole, putting a nut in it,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.16,0:31:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and he'd run back and dig another hole, and he was in a panic,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.85,0:31:05.01,Default,,0,0,0,,that while he was digging a hole here, somebody might take his nuts.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.09,0:31:05.77,Default,,0,0,0,,He just went crazy.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.50,0:31:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,He would fit in today's world very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.68,0:31:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Bacteria, all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.50,0:31:16.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So the core, the essence of life, the source of life,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.11,0:31:19.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and this is the illusion you have to give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.77,0:31:22.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The last doorway.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.01,0:31:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The last doorway, what you're giving up is the experience of this
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.11,0:31:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,as the core of essence.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.83,0:31:32.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The essence of life and truth, because that's the way it has always been.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.79,0:31:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And that is what you lay down to God at the last.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.00,0:31:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you find that the source of life is the radiance of divinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.59,0:31:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But in the experiential world, it comes from getting this.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.14,0:31:53.33,Default,,0,0,0,,The first invertebrates, Susie gave me a trilobite one time
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.44,0:31:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,for Father's Day or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.47,0:31:58.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The trilobite calibrated at six or eight.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.72,0:32:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Then it evolves, the level of consciousness up to 12,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.11,0:32:05.81,Default,,0,0,0,,many marine invertebrates.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.72,0:32:08.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's the trilobite here.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.31,0:32:10.01,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a smart trilobite.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.11,0:32:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Mine must have been a dumb one.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.21,0:32:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,This guy's up to 12.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.63,0:32:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,How did he get there?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.48,0:32:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, this is an old dictionary.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.88,0:32:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.38,0:32:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. First traces of life, scorpions.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.03,0:32:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Scorpions, I once wrote a book about it,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.24,0:32:28.74,Default,,0,0,0,,because I was an etymologist at one time in my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.33,0:32:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And the scorpion crawled out of the sea 400 million years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.53,0:32:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Scorpion crawled out of the sea, became a land creature,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.35,0:32:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and calibrates at 17.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.74,0:32:45.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Snails, brachiopods, up to 27.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.74,0:32:50.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is the calibrated level of the totality of all life on the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.70,0:32:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not exactly concordant with other things,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.09,0:32:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,because this is all of life, represents all of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.38,0:33:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So here we have the scorpion, the first amphibians.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.43,0:33:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Here we have the shell-crushing sharks,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.93,0:33:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,the first reptiles, amphibious,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.32,0:33:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,the rise of the reptiles,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.26,0:33:18.17,Default,,0,0,0,,rise of the dinosaurs in the 60s.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.53,0:33:22.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The dinosaurs are in the 60s.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.74,0:33:28.59,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of the people we're dealing with politically are 60.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.46,0:33:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you like to sign a treaty and become a,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.51,0:33:40.01,Default,,0,0,0,,what do you call our form of government?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.79,0:33:42.29,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.48,0:33:44.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, democracy.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.77,0:33:46.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you like democracy?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.17,0:33:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Can I eat it?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.89,0:33:59.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Can I kill people with it?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.78,0:34:01.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Can I be a hero with it?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.43,0:34:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,A little hard to sell it to these people here.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.73,0:34:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Democracy to a shell-crushing shark.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.63,0:34:19.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You people are the leaders of the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.82,0:34:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You get the reality of international diplomacy,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.53,0:34:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,then you get what survival's about,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.63,0:34:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and you see it isn't truth, it's how you present the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.73,0:34:29.82,Default,,0,0,0,,How you present the truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.21,0:34:33.82,Default,,0,0,0,,it's either going to look good to eat or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.01,0:34:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the core of the ego here is to eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.01,0:34:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, the only reason anybody would be interested in
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.82,0:34:43.51,Default,,0,0,0,,our form of government is what do we get out of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.63,0:34:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.15,0:34:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You got to come from where they are, hungry people.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.50,0:34:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Give me your gun and vote for this form of government.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.90,0:34:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Give me a break.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.69,0:34:55.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, the naivety of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.28,0:34:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.30,0:35:03.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I try to bring spiritual truth into actually an understanding
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.23,0:35:05.13,Default,,0,0,0,,is not just an abstract goody-goody.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.32,0:35:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's part of the totality of all of life
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.32,0:35:10.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and our experience of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.23,0:35:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore your perception of it is quite different
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.73,0:35:19.23,Default,,0,0,0,,if you have a greater understanding of consciousness and spiritual truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.96,0:35:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of decrying it or vilifying it,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.86,0:35:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,you can say this person must have some karmic reason to go through this.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.05,0:35:31.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And we all must be learning something through this experience
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.55,0:35:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,because all of humanity jointly learns
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.15,0:35:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and speaks, learns truth jointly.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.48,0:35:41.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you see the rise of the reptiles, rise of the dinosaurs,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.57,0:35:48.67,Default,,0,0,0,,first birds, primitive mammals, the last of the dinosaurs.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.07,0:35:49.98,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what they think.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.40,0:35:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,They thought they lived.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.19,0:35:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.90,0:36:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And you see the evolution of animals, modern animals and plants together to the 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.30,0:36:04.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And finally, mankind in the last flick of an eyelid.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.03,0:36:07.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The last flick of an eyelid of evolutionary time
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.92,0:36:10.82,Default,,0,0,0,,is so brief that it hardly shows up on the chart.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.92,0:36:15.53,Default,,0,0,0,,That hardly, approximate duration in millions of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.63,0:36:18.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, we're not even on the chart yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.63,0:36:21.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The human evolution is so minuscule.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.63,0:36:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,That gives us a different feeling of the evolution of time when we say
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.63,0:36:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,the spirit, the soul, karma evolves over great eons of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.11,0:36:36.23,Default,,0,0,0,,In as much as we got born as humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.44,0:36:38.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And the human has a physicality.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.59,0:36:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,This is how far back the ego goes.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.63,0:36:51.23,Default,,0,0,0,,This is how far back the ego goes.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.17,0:36:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,70% of archeologic time had already transpired
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.98,0:37:00.28,Default,,0,0,0,,before consciousness level was even at one.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.11,0:37:06.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That gives us a certain patience with our own ego and a certain respect for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.21,0:37:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Your ego was born before trilobites.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.32,0:37:16.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see if that's a fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.78,0:37:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The ego birthed before trilobites existed.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.96,0:37:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.96,0:37:33.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The ego was already on its way in the very beginning of archeologic time.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.34,0:37:39.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, so it's sort of a dinosaur-y kind of thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.63,0:37:41.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, sort of a primitive kind of a thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.63,0:37:42.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.63,0:37:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,What does this primitive kind of thing do?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.23,0:37:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, now we understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.40,0:37:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,His name is Ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.19,0:37:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Ego is a human being.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.05,0:37:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's buried in the back of the human brain then.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.67,0:38:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So when man developed the prefrontal cortex,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.67,0:38:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,they didn't remove the old animal brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.11,0:38:07.01,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.11,0:38:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,They plastered it on top of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.09,0:38:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you got an animal that can think.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.94,0:38:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You just gave a retarded kid a gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.17,0:38:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't get into trouble, Junior.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.17,0:38:27.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't aim it at anybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.17,0:38:28.57,Default,,0,0,0,,No, Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.57,0:38:32.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Bladdle, bladdle, bladdle.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.71,0:38:37.46,Default,,0,0,0,,War is giving the ego a gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.55,0:38:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.42,0:38:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so how do I understand that which has been here
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.42,0:38:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,since the very beginning of earthly time almost,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.42,0:38:50.28,Default,,0,0,0,,not earthly time, but living time,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.38,0:38:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,is I get what it is by understanding how it evolved.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.11,0:38:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I now, instead of vilifying it,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.44,0:39:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I see that the ego is doing what it's supposed to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.50,0:39:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Get.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.50,0:39:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Get more money.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.50,0:39:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Get more prestige.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.50,0:39:07.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Get more cars.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.50,0:39:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Get more ladies in bed with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.50,0:39:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.50,0:39:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Get more time on TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.98,0:39:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Be a bigger celebrity.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.98,0:39:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Get a bigger house.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.98,0:39:17.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Get a BMW.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.11,0:39:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,No, you don't do that in the bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.48,0:39:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You thought BMW meant the bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.48,0:39:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,No, that's not the bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.88,0:39:26.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a car.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.88,0:39:34.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so you own it instead of negating it.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.07,0:39:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I approve of the workbook of the Course in Miracles,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.07,0:39:39.98,Default,,0,0,0,,but not textbook.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.07,0:39:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Because textbook deteriorates.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.98,0:39:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It goes from 600 down to 550.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.98,0:39:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.98,0:39:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it begins to vilify
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.98,0:39:51.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and get into a dualistic relationship with the ego thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.30,0:39:55.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and you can't beat the ego by getting positionalized about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.38,0:39:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You can only dissolve it by owning it.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.42,0:40:02.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You're born with the karma within.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.96,0:40:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The animal only can survive if it gets.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.57,0:40:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,A human being cannot survive without getting.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.57,0:40:13.71,Default,,0,0,0,,His body can't survive without getting.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.92,0:40:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to get food.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.92,0:40:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, if we were green, we wouldn't have to be the way we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.92,0:40:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Go sit in the sun?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.88,0:40:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, no, we have to go for lunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.73,0:40:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Ego, you're hungry, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.38,0:40:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,He's hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.38,0:40:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And what will happen if I don't feed you?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.38,0:40:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I will die.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.38,0:40:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, no wonder he's so panicky.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.38,0:40:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, don't do a BM there.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.98,0:40:49.88,Default,,0,0,0,,We're just sitting on the table.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.98,0:40:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.98,0:40:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,How long do we have for lunch?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.94,0:40:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.28,0:40:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.73,0:41:28.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So, shall we discontinue now and re-continue afterwards?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.80,0:41:29.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Appearance is not essence.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.80,0:41:35.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The cover is not the book.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.30,0:41:39.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we were understanding how the ego developed over time
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.36,0:41:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,as a necessity of survival.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.88,0:41:46.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Consequently, it's trained to get.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.40,0:41:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We call that the solar plexus fixation.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.51,0:41:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,When it's dominated by that solar plexus energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.42,0:41:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,it cannot be satisfied.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.42,0:41:56.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.61,0:41:59.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the problem is not wanting that.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.61,0:42:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's wanting-ness.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.67,0:42:04.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You cannot satisfy wanting-ness by satisfying it.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.67,0:42:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You only feed it more.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.67,0:42:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The more money you make, the more money you have to have.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.90,0:42:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Millions is not enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.90,0:42:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Multi-millions is not enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.90,0:42:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Billions is not enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.75,0:42:17.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Going to bed with one maid is not enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.75,0:42:18.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Ten is not enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.75,0:42:19.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Thirty is not enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.75,0:42:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,There are men that have gone to bed with hundreds.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.75,0:42:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Their only lament is they're too old now.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.26,0:42:36.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, after 450 women, you haven't satisfied your curiosity yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.26,0:42:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So you cannot satisfy it.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.59,0:42:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So once the energy gets caught in the solar plexus,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.59,0:42:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,you're stuck below 200 of wanting-ness and craving-ness.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.59,0:42:47.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you're wanting and craving it,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.98,0:42:49.88,Default,,0,0,0,,it looks like you're being deprived.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.98,0:42:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So you hear the disgruntled people in the world
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.98,0:42:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,that are always complaining how they're deprived.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.98,0:42:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because their wanting-ness cannot be satisfied.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.34,0:43:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not satisfy-able.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.23,0:43:04.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Not satisfy-able.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.26,0:43:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So they fault everything in society.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.30,0:43:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The current favorite target is America
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.30,0:43:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and all of its establishments
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.40,0:43:13.30,Default,,0,0,0,,because they're coming from,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.40,0:43:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,they feel sensitive and uncomfortable and deprived.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.40,0:43:18.36,Default,,0,0,0,,They need a psychiatrist.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.46,0:43:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,They really don't have to change the United States Constitution.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.46,0:43:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,They need a doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.46,0:43:26.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So whether it's Wal-Mart or whatever it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.55,0:43:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So, all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.44,0:43:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,That comes from a distortion which we'll get into later.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.44,0:43:39.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Called the distorted hermeneutics of relativistic epistemology.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.48,0:43:45.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Which you have to know to understand society.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.71,0:43:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it's a whole chapter in a book.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.51,0:43:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Hermeneutics.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.51,0:43:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Hermeneutics means the meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.51,0:43:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Meaning, science of meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.51,0:43:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Relativistic epistemology.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.42,0:44:04.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And the secret of understanding it is given by the mad hatter.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.46,0:44:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Who says things will just mean what I want them to mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.36,0:44:10.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.61,0:44:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The denial of the absolute.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.09,0:44:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The denial of logic, reason, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.01,0:44:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The denial, it's actually the denial of divinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.01,0:44:28.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It comes out of the narcissistic ego which wants to be God.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.01,0:44:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And wishes to replace God and become God.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.01,0:44:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.01,0:44:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.01,0:44:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll get to that later this afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.01,0:44:37.78,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.88,0:44:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So we saw how for life to evolve,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.78,0:44:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,it had to be get.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.78,0:44:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It had to be want.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.78,0:44:47.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So wantingness and gettingness is intrinsic to the ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.82,0:44:50.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And then when you add a prefrontal cortex,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.82,0:44:53.71,Default,,0,0,0,,you get the what of the gettingness and the wantingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.82,0:44:57.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Fame, fortune, more money, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.82,0:45:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can't satisfy him because...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.28,0:45:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Because what?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.28,0:45:08.09,Default,,0,0,0,,He wants all of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.19,0:45:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,He wants all the women in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.05,0:45:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,All the money.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.01,0:45:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,All the power.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:17.01,0:45:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So he's doing a good job.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.40,0:45:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,When you want something more, you know he's doing a good job.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.40,0:45:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So you say, you're doing a good job.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.40,0:45:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,They cut in front of you, they deserve to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:36.88,0:45:38.05,Default,,0,0,0,,We hate them.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.15,0:45:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.15,0:45:40.05,Default,,0,0,0,,We hate them.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.15,0:45:41.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So you own it.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.73,0:45:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,When you own it and stop resisting it, you dissolve it.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.73,0:45:48.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You dissolve it because oppositionalism gives it energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:48.63,0:45:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So that which is not truth, why give it a reality by resisting it and opposing it?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.57,0:46:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,That is the way of traditional religion.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.92,0:46:01.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Traditional religion.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.92,0:46:04.82,Default,,0,0,0,,How many enlightened people have occurred on the planet?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.92,0:46:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Hardly any.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.92,0:46:11.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The difficulty is that God is not at the bottom of the chart.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.82,0:46:14.71,Default,,0,0,0,,He's at the top of the chart.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.82,0:46:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Joy, forgiveness, happiness, thankfulness, not at the bottom.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.98,0:46:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,But at the top.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.88,0:46:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.88,0:46:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Generosity instead of greed.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.88,0:46:26.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll move on now.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.88,0:46:28.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We've seen how it evolved.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:28.88,0:46:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And we've done the animals before.
