Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.65,0:51:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Their consciousness is aligned with a common attractor field.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.65,0:51:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a attractor field.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.65,0:51:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,There's only one cat in the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.67,0:51:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And then that cat energy, that awareness, which is where intelligence learns from experience,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.00,0:51:42.11,Default,,0,0,0,,occurs, is on the level of consciousness, in that attractor field.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:42.21,0:51:49.15,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so these animals inherit the karmic consequence of that attractor field,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.25,0:51:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,which we'll learn later is the same with people who calibrate below 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.25,0:52:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Like an animal, they do not have a personal etheric brain, personal karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:00.59,0:52:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,They join in the group karma of that energy field.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:03.96,0:52:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you're born a mackerel, you see the deep-sea,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.86,0:52:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,pictures of the mackerel, they swirl like a big doughnut in the water.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:12.86,0:52:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Hundreds of thousands of them congregate.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.86,0:52:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,They're following one single attractor field.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.86,0:52:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,They are not individual consciousness following each other like pilots in formation.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.59,0:52:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,They are not like pilot formation.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:28.59,0:52:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Each one of them is individually aligned with that energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:52:32.59,0:52:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and is following that field within himself, each one,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:36.94,0:52:42.84,Default,,0,0,0,,which has certain consequences.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:43.03,0:52:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,There are certain consequences in human history,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.94,0:52:50.84,Default,,0,0,0,,where people below 200 are now led as though they have one mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.94,0:52:53.13,Default,,0,0,0,,not too intelligent either.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.23,0:52:57.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Because to be intelligent, you have to be over 200 and be able to think for yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.23,0:52:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see group think.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.42,0:53:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You see 70 million people going,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.55,0:53:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Sighail, Sighail, Sighail, Sighail.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.55,0:53:08.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What are they, automatons?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.55,0:53:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Have they lost the capacity to think, to reason? What?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.84,0:53:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,If you've got the capacity to think or reason,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.84,0:53:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,you get exterminated.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:15.73,0:53:19.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So in every revolution, intellectuals are the first ones to be killed,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.73,0:53:23.07,Default,,0,0,0,,because they might object.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.17,0:53:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:25.40,0:53:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,No, the way you take over a society is first by distorting logic,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.40,0:53:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,captivating the intellectuals of the academic world.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:33.40,0:53:36.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And so you start from there,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:36.46,0:53:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,so that when you start coming up with various things,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.46,0:53:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,their objection has already been silenced.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:43.13,0:53:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so you see dogs go up five points.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.03,0:53:49.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Gorillas, chimpanzees.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:49.26,0:53:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Alex is a great parrot at 4.01, and is on the internet.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.26,0:53:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And I forget, Dr. Pepperdine, I think, is the one, University of Tucson.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:58.26,0:54:01.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You see Coco at 4.05.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.26,0:54:06.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And so you see, the question is, can animals think?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:06.26,0:54:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,400 says yes, they can think.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:08.26,0:54:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,All the arguments about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.48,0:54:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The songbird song.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:12.48,0:54:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's three strange exceptions,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.38,0:54:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and we've never gotten the karmic reasons for this.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.38,0:54:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The songbird's song calibrates at 500.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.38,0:54:25.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The cat's purr calibrates at 500.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:25.19,0:54:28.09,Default,,0,0,0,,See, the cat is up here as a being,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.19,0:54:32.09,Default,,0,0,0,,but its purr somehow channels some kind of an other energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.19,0:54:35.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And the dog's wagging tail calibrates at 500.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:35.19,0:54:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Universal love. Universal love. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:39.40,0:54:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Friendly dog just loves everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:42.40,0:54:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Friendly kitty, off to pet it, and there's the purr.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:45.51,0:54:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So that is strange indeed, is it not?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:48.59,0:54:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. So we'll go on to the next thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:52.78,0:54:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I already told you my horse karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.90,0:55:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I had very bad horse karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:00.90,0:55:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I finally overcame it, and I avoided horses for years.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.90,0:55:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'd overcome it anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.94,0:55:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So I went over to meet this new horse,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:08.94,0:55:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and I never had a kiss from a horse in my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.94,0:55:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,He gave me a kiss.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.94,0:55:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a great karmic moment where I ended my negative karma with horses.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:17.94,0:55:20.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been thrown 20 times, I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:20.94,0:55:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. On to the next.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.55,0:55:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. You see, spiritual foundation.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.51,0:55:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, when we talk about the Chinese fortune cookie,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:31.51,0:55:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,those who are spiritually evolved see the wisdom involved.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:35.86,0:55:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,See the wisdom involved.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.86,0:55:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The basic spiritual foundations from 200 and up,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.86,0:55:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,you see, have to do with ethics and morality.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.86,0:55:49.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Ethics and morality are under vociferous attack right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:50.01,0:55:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And what are the basic spiritual things from which we take off?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:54.92,0:55:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,What you see in front of you is really the Boy Scouts,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.92,0:56:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,the Girl Scouts, the 4-H Club, the Elks.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:00.96,0:56:05.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the backbone of what is now called traditional America.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:11.86,0:56:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Consideration for others.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:15.01,0:56:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And when I grew up in the Midwest in traditional America,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:18.01,0:56:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,we thought there's only two kinds of people.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.01,0:56:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,There's these kind of people who are decent, honest, friendly, polite,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:24.11,0:56:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and then there's criminals.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:27.21,0:56:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all there was.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:29.21,0:56:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,There was Babyface Nelson, John Dillinger,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:32.28,0:56:35.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Scarface in Chicago, Capone.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:35.28,0:56:38.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And then there was normal people.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.30,0:56:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what we thought all there was on the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:41.59,0:56:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You go to church on Sunday, you don't steal.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:44.59,0:56:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,If you break any rules, you get stricken with guilt.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.63,0:56:51.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You go into a whole big guilt thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:51.63,0:56:54.53,Default,,0,0,0,,But we thought everybody was reliable and honest
Dialogue: 0,0:56:54.63,0:56:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and did hard work.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:56.53,0:56:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody was moral.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.53,0:57:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody was helpful.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:00.53,0:57:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And then there was cranky old guys,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:02.53,0:57:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,but you know, you made an exception for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:04.90,0:57:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And everybody was expected to be thoughtful.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:06.90,0:57:09.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, they'd leave the toilet seat up or down.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:15.53,0:57:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody persisted.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:17.53,0:57:20.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You just didn't give up like a weak nilly about everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:20.53,0:57:22.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We were all tolerant.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:22.53,0:57:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know, I didn't experience or witness
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.53,0:57:26.67,Default,,0,0,0,,any racial prejudice at all when I grew up.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:26.86,0:57:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I never saw it.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.96,0:57:30.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Black people would be loved because they were black.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:30.96,0:57:33.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Chinese people would be loved because they were Chinese.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:33.96,0:57:35.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody was just loved for what they were.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:35.96,0:57:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And so there wasn't even any,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:38.98,0:57:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,that kind of class distinction or whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.30,0:57:45.21,Default,,0,0,0,,That was traditional America.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:45.30,0:57:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,People were dependable.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:46.30,0:57:47.21,Default,,0,0,0,,They were really genuine.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:47.30,0:57:49.21,Default,,0,0,0,,They were who they were.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:49.30,0:57:52.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody was expected to be stable and honorable.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:52.34,0:57:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,When a woman entered the room, we all stood up in respect.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:56.23,0:58:00.13,Default,,0,0,0,,We were part of honoring femininity.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:00.46,0:58:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody was sort of neat.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:02.46,0:58:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And we considered this normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:05.46,0:58:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So normal calibrates at 300.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:08.46,0:58:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,We assumed, unless declared otherwise,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:11.46,0:58:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,that everybody was sane, fair, run by ethics,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:15.46,0:58:18.36,Default,,0,0,0,,did what they could to be healthy, a sense of humor.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:18.46,0:58:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people got left out of that, but we avoided them
Dialogue: 0,0:58:22.46,0:58:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,,because they were going to be dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:24.46,0:58:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,He never laughed at anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:27.50,0:58:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, God, the word went out.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:30.40,0:58:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't try joking around Uncle Busbo.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:33.40,0:58:36.76,Default,,0,0,0,,He's been seeing a doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:36.86,0:58:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Sense of humor, loyal, equitable.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:39.86,0:58:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,We call this wisdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.86,0:58:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So here you got wisdom at 385.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:43.86,0:58:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to be a rocket scientist
Dialogue: 0,0:58:45.86,0:58:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,to begin to look to wisdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.86,0:58:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Before you make a decision, you say,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.44,0:58:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,this may be the right thing to do,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:53.44,0:58:55.34,Default,,0,0,0,,this may be the correct thing to do,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.44,0:58:56.34,Default,,0,0,0,,but is it wisdom?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:56.44,0:58:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,In writing this book, I ran across that endlessly.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:59.53,0:59:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it wise?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:01.44,0:59:03.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Does it serve mankind?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:03.44,0:59:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Does it serve my obligation to God to reveal this or not?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:10.44,0:59:13.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And if so, how to contextualize it
Dialogue: 0,0:59:13.44,0:59:18.17,Default,,0,0,0,,so as to be as less upsetting?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:18.28,0:59:23.21,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so wisdom then was constantly part of the thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:23.30,0:59:26.21,Default,,0,0,0,,To be loyal to God and to truth, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:26.30,0:59:29.21,Default,,0,0,0,,At the same time,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:29.21,0:59:34.11,Default,,0,0,0,,ask, yes, but is it wise and rational?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:34.21,0:59:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it wise?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:35.21,0:59:36.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it intelligent?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:36.21,0:59:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Does it support life?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:38.21,0:59:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it intrinsically benign?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:41.90,0:59:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it really protective of life?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:43.90,0:59:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it humane to share what you've learned?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:47.09,0:59:51.15,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so pleasing means a certain ambiance.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:51.26,0:59:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't mean codependency.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:54.26,1:00:00.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Glad, happy, sensible, pleasant, positive.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:00.28,1:00:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,We call these wisdom.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:02.34,1:00:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so what does it mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:04.78,1:00:07.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it means to follow the earth at 240.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:07.78,1:00:09.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Relatively modest.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:09.78,1:00:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You try to phrase things in a way diplomatically.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:12.98,1:00:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, you will have to be beheaded later today, Dave.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:19.13,1:00:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,However, you can have whatever you like for lunch.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:24.98,1:00:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And in those lifetimes, I said to the husband,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:27.98,1:00:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,don't worry, it's your job.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:30.53,1:00:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't feel bad about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:34.73,1:00:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:35.73,1:00:37.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You won't collect the Social Security if it doesn't.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:37.73,1:00:38.63,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:38.63,1:00:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Be polite.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:40.69,1:00:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,At the same time, you're not wishy-washy.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:42.69,1:00:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You could be faulted for being wishy-washy.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:45.69,1:00:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,At the same time, you were nice.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:47.69,1:00:49.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You were nice, but not wishy-washy.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:49.69,1:00:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's the way in which you contextualize the thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:53.69,1:00:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The way you present it is with consideration for the audience.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:57.69,1:01:00.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And as we said, Aristotle's pathos,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:00.82,1:01:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,to be aware of the impact of your behaviors
Dialogue: 0,1:01:04.82,1:01:06.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and your statements on others.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:06.73,1:01:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And to say, is it wise?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:08.73,1:01:10.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Does it serve the good of mankind?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:10.73,1:01:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Does it serve God?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:12.73,1:01:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So wisdom then, as you get more spiritually advanced,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.73,1:01:18.63,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes a little more complex.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:18.73,1:01:21.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Because from this viewpoint, it might look this way.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:21.98,1:01:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,From this viewpoint, another way.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:24.98,1:01:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And that whole concept of codependency comes in there, you see.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:29.17,1:01:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:30.17,1:01:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll move on to the next one.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:32.17,1:01:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,But we thought everybody was this way.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:34.17,1:01:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody grew up in Midwest?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:37.07,1:01:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Midwest, wasn't that the way it was?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:41.07,1:01:43.09,Default,,0,0,0,,We thought everybody was that way,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:43.19,1:01:45.09,Default,,0,0,0,,except for John Dillinger and Al Capone.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:45.19,1:01:51.23,Default,,0,0,0,,This is too much of a brain picture.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:51.32,1:01:53.23,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll move on to the next brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:53.32,1:01:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:57.78,1:02:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we said that under 200,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:00.78,1:02:02.69,Default,,0,0,0,,a person does not even have an etheric brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:02.78,1:02:05.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And I didn't even know whether to put that in the book.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:06.03,1:02:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,But under 200, people share a group karma,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:09.03,1:02:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,the attractor field of that group.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:10.94,1:02:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So if, let's say, you're hateful,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:14.38,1:02:18.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and you do that to get your life to hatefulness,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:18.38,1:02:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,then your consciousness is dominated by the attractor field
Dialogue: 0,1:02:22.38,1:02:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,to which you have ascribed.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:24.38,1:02:27.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That to which you commit, then.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:27.71,1:02:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You are under the dominance of that attractor field.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:30.71,1:02:32.71,Default,,0,0,0,,That attractor field.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:32.80,1:02:37.05,Default,,0,0,0,,That attractor field under 200, then,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:37.15,1:02:41.05,Default,,0,0,0,,expresses itself in brain physiology up here as left brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:41.05,1:02:48.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The animal brain, ego's brain is the left brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:48.11,1:02:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And how is that?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:50.30,1:02:52.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The input from the world,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:52.30,1:02:55.19,Default,,0,0,0,,whether it's television or somebody bumping into you.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:55.30,1:02:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, somebody bumped into us at lunch, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:58.32,1:03:00.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And, well, it was an accident.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:00.32,1:03:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,We both apologized to each other.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:02.32,1:03:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't want her to feel upset.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:04.32,1:03:06.23,Default,,0,0,0,,She didn't want us to feel upset.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:06.32,1:03:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,We were concerned with each other's happiness and welfare, etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:10.59,1:03:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:12.48,1:03:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Left brain would go into an outrage.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:14.48,1:03:16.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the left brain input,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:16.48,1:03:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,the fast track is to the thalamus, a relay station.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:20.48,1:03:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The fast track is to the emotional centers
Dialogue: 0,1:03:24.48,1:03:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and what's called the amygdala, the emotional.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:27.48,1:03:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So the fast track is perception.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:29.48,1:03:33.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Perception sees it, fast tracks it
Dialogue: 0,1:03:33.48,1:03:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,through the animal interpretation of perception
Dialogue: 0,1:03:38.90,1:03:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and then stores that memory in the hippocampus.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:42.90,1:03:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,As I say, I always like hippocampus.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:45.90,1:03:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It's somewhere in Mississippi or Missouri.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:48.90,1:03:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Hippocampus, Missouri.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:50.90,1:03:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, so the fast track then is left brain, fast track.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:57.13,1:04:00.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever happened to reason and intelligence
Dialogue: 0,1:04:00.13,1:04:02.03,Default,,0,0,0,,in the good book of wisdom you read?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:02.13,1:04:04.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that's in your frontal cortex.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:04.13,1:04:09.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And unfortunately, the frontal cortex in these people is slow.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:09.13,1:04:11.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Slow.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:11.19,1:04:13.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You've already pulled the trigger
Dialogue: 0,1:04:13.09,1:04:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're like, maybe I should have thought about that.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:19.09,1:04:21.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Oops.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:21.25,1:04:23.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Oops.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:23.25,1:04:25.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So these people are subject to oops.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:25.25,1:04:27.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And they come back from New York and they say,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:27.25,1:04:29.15,Default,,0,0,0,,boy, isn't that an awful place?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:29.25,1:04:31.15,Default,,0,0,0,,They're all so impolite there and rude.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:31.25,1:04:35.15,Default,,0,0,0,,They're all out to cheat you and all that.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:35.25,1:04:37.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So the left brain person,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:37.25,1:04:39.15,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness level below 200,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:39.25,1:04:41.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I want you to have some compassion for it
Dialogue: 0,1:04:41.25,1:04:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,because that's the way the experience is.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:43.25,1:04:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how they experience the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:45.51,1:04:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not just malevolence.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:48.01,1:04:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,But that's how they experience the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:50.17,1:04:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,They see it in a distorted way.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:52.17,1:04:57.57,Default,,0,0,0,,They see America as the great Satan, let's say.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:57.67,1:05:04.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Because their brain physiology interprets everything this way.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:04.15,1:05:06.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And they'll say, well, I also read the good book.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:06.15,1:05:09.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, but the good book is stored over here in the cortex,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:09.15,1:05:11.05,Default,,0,0,0,,which you don't listen to.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:11.15,1:05:14.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You listen to your animal.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:14.21,1:05:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,First kill them, then remember the good book.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:17.21,1:05:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:19.44,1:05:22.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So below 200, you have a different physiology,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:22.44,1:05:24.34,Default,,0,0,0,,different brain function,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:24.44,1:05:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,different karmic mechanism.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:26.44,1:05:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It's group, attractor-fueled karma.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:29.44,1:05:32.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The prefrontal cortex, as you see,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:32.53,1:05:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,is plastered onto this old animal brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:35.53,1:05:37.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's the animal brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:37.80,1:05:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And now you just plastered this onto it.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:41.01,1:05:43.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's slow.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:43.11,1:05:45.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And people have psychopathic personalities.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:45.21,1:05:47.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Sociopathic personalities.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:47.11,1:05:50.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The actual thickness of the prefrontal cortex
Dialogue: 0,1:05:50.11,1:05:52.01,Default,,0,0,0,,is actually less than normal people.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:52.11,1:05:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Congenitally, anatomically unable to be socially responsible.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:58.11,1:05:59.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:59.11,1:06:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Impaired.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:02.53,1:06:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, what we see as perpetrator out there
Dialogue: 0,1:06:04.53,1:06:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,is actually, when you look at it differently, the victim.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:08.53,1:06:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The vicious, psychopathic, narcissistic, middle-of-the-maniac
Dialogue: 0,1:06:13.46,1:06:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,that leads 10 million people to death
Dialogue: 0,1:06:16.36,1:06:21.05,Default,,0,0,0,,is literally also the victim.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:21.15,1:06:25.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The perpetrator, then, is the victim of falsity.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:25.78,1:06:28.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't have enough evolution of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:06:28.78,1:06:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,to discern truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:31.01,1:06:33.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Is therefore the victim of propaganda.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:34.01,1:06:36.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is how Joseph Goebbels got his power.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:37.17,1:06:39.38,Default,,0,0,0,,He knew this.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:39.48,1:06:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,He knew this.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:41.48,1:06:45.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You can condition the animal to see things that way.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:45.80,1:06:48.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:48.98,1:06:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness level below 200 is left brain dominance.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:54.05,1:06:57.01,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a linear Newtonian world.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:57.11,1:07:01.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It releases constant stress, adrenaline, fight or flight,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:01.11,1:07:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,alarm reaction, Selye's alarm reaction,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:05.21,1:07:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,the release of the canon fight or flight pathway,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:10.34,1:07:14.07,Default,,0,0,0,,adrenaline, cortisone,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:14.17,1:07:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and that's how you perforate your ulcer.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:17.17,1:07:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Being an alarm reaction all the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:20.26,1:07:24.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So during the accident, which came on just an hour ago,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:24.26,1:07:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,the alarm reaction was about that fast.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:27.40,1:07:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we looked at each other.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:29.40,1:07:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It was like recognizing the energy of the other person.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:32.40,1:07:34.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And we all said,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:34.69,1:07:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,ah, forget the insurance company, nobody got hurt.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:37.69,1:07:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Instant forgiveness, instant so what?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:40.69,1:07:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Instant capacity.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:42.69,1:07:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? Because the etheric brain is functional.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:45.78,1:07:49.75,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so in this left brain person, who is an animal,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:49.75,1:07:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,the thymus is under stress.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:52.19,1:07:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why you have to do the Dr. Diamond's thymic thump.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:55.19,1:08:00.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Because right now, after that,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:00.19,1:08:03.09,Default,,0,0,0,,your acupuncture system got blown out.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:03.19,1:08:05.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Your acupuncture system.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:05.67,1:08:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So the ordinary person, left brain, who got rear-ended,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:09.67,1:08:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,will go into this, blow their acupuncture meridian,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:12.67,1:08:15.57,Default,,0,0,0,,end up with indignation and rage.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:15.67,1:08:17.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Indignation and rage.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:17.68,1:08:21.88,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:21.88,1:08:24.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So the left brain person is under thymic stress.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:24.88,1:08:29.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The depression of the thymus results in less circulating
Dialogue: 0,1:08:29.19,1:08:31.10,Default,,0,0,0,,so-called killer cells and immunity.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:31.19,1:08:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The killer cells are the good guys, despite their name.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:34.19,1:08:36.10,Default,,0,0,0,,They kill bugs.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:36.19,1:08:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,They kill germs.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:38.19,1:08:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So you lose your immunity.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:40.19,1:08:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not able to fight off infection.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:42.19,1:08:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You catch colds and viruses.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:44.19,1:08:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And these people walk into the same crowd as you did.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:48.19,1:08:51.10,Default,,0,0,0,,But out of 100 people here, only three get a cold.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:51.10,1:08:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Over here, 72 get a cold.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:53.10,1:08:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Quite a difference.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:54.10,1:08:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So the immune system, you see, is impaired.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:57.10,1:09:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The brain neurotransmitters here, you deplete the serotonin level.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:03.10,1:09:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why you see a psychiatrist.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:05.10,1:09:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He puts you on something to rebuild the serotonin level.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:08.10,1:09:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The track to the emotions is twice as fast
Dialogue: 0,1:09:11.28,1:09:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,as through the cerebral cortex to the emotions.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:14.28,1:09:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:15.28,1:09:17.53,Default,,0,0,0,,That's quite a different world.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:17.64,1:09:19.53,Default,,0,0,0,,49% of America.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:19.64,1:09:21.53,Default,,0,0,0,,85% of the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:21.64,1:09:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Lives along this track here.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:24.57,1:09:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So when you present something to other cultures,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:27.57,1:09:30.47,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to know what is the calibrated level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:09:30.57,1:09:33.47,Default,,0,0,0,,because you want to know, is this side of the brain even working?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:33.96,1:09:35.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it even working?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:38.38,1:09:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Many of the cultures we've dealt with,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:40.38,1:09:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,this side of the brain isn't even working yet.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:44.23,1:09:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You're telling about the superiority of a governmental system
Dialogue: 0,1:09:47.23,1:09:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,when these people are living here.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:50.23,1:09:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You see why diplomacy very often has failed.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:53.50,1:09:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:55.39,1:09:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:56.39,1:09:58.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So this side, the right brain dominance,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:58.39,1:10:00.28,Default,,0,0,0,,now above consciousness level 200,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:00.39,1:10:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,it now becomes a right brain track predominantly.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:04.39,1:10:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The input now is fast through the etheric brain
Dialogue: 0,1:10:10.39,1:10:12.28,Default,,0,0,0,,to the emotional center
Dialogue: 0,1:10:12.39,1:10:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,because at 200 now, one develops an etheric brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:16.39,1:10:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Aetheric brain is not protoplasmic.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:19.39,1:10:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It exists of pure energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:22.28,1:10:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,People who think they are protoplasm
Dialogue: 0,1:10:24.80,1:10:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,have a hard time understanding etheric brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:27.80,1:10:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, well, you don't have any problem understanding your radio set.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:30.80,1:10:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, you know, invisible energy fields, TV.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:34.80,1:10:38.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole world is made up of invisible, non-protoplasmic,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:38.80,1:10:44.76,Default,,0,0,0,,non-measurable, non-physical energy field frequencies and vibrations.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:44.85,1:10:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And when it comes to consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:46.89,1:10:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,not only the very advanced high frequency vibrations,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:49.89,1:10:54.78,Default,,0,0,0,,but even beyond them, there are octaves beyond them.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:54.89,1:11:01.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So above 200, then, you get the rise of kundalini energy,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:02.00,1:11:03.93,Default,,0,0,0,,what's called kundalini energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:04.03,1:11:08.53,Default,,0,0,0,,That is from a little culture called kundalini energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:08.64,1:11:12.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't favor it because it sounds foreign to Americans.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:12.64,1:11:15.69,Default,,0,0,0,,A spiritual energy then arises
Dialogue: 0,1:11:15.80,1:11:18.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and begins to flow up tracks in the spine.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:18.80,1:11:22.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The east, the hot and the cold, the east and the west tracks,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:22.80,1:11:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and they've got fancy Sanskrit names,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:24.80,1:11:26.98,Default,,0,0,0,,which you can live without.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:26.98,1:11:29.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, the energy flows up the spine,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:29.98,1:11:34.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and as your consciousness gets into the 500s,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:34.98,1:11:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,maybe around 540, I would guess around 540,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:37.98,1:11:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,around 4 or 540, let's see, unconditional love, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:42.11,1:11:47.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It begins to experience it about 540, over 540, at 540.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:47.11,1:11:49.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, okay, unconditional love then,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:49.60,1:11:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,because much to your surprise, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:52.60,1:11:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,not having read anything about it or heard anything about it,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:55.60,1:11:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,you begin to notice this exquisite sensation
Dialogue: 0,1:11:57.60,1:11:59.39,Default,,0,0,0,,going up your spine, going up your back.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:59.50,1:12:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It flows up your back,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:01.81,1:12:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and strangely it flows into your brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:03.81,1:12:07.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It went on for six years, I think.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:08.06,1:12:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This exquisite energy, better than an orgasm, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:12.10,1:12:14.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Better in quality.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:14.52,1:12:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Very close to the experience of the presence of divinity
Dialogue: 0,1:12:18.52,1:12:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,when I was in a snow bank, age 12 or 14.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:22.52,1:12:27.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The meltingness of the exquisiteness of this field prevails,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:27.52,1:12:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and you feel the same,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:29.60,1:12:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,the same exquisite energy flowing up your back.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:35.11,1:12:37.02,Default,,0,0,0,,If you think about, if you focus your attention
Dialogue: 0,1:12:37.11,1:12:39.02,Default,,0,0,0,,on the left side of your brain, it flows on the left side.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:39.11,1:12:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,If you focus on the right, it flows on the right side.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:42.18,1:12:44.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It's absolutely exquisite.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:45.07,1:12:47.97,Default,,0,0,0,,This energy, as I've written about in books,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:48.07,1:12:50.27,Default,,0,0,0,,acts on its own.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:50.36,1:12:53.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It has nothing to do with you as a person or volitional.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:53.56,1:12:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It may flow out to an automobile wreck
Dialogue: 0,1:12:57.56,1:12:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,where people are praying,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:59.46,1:13:02.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and it flows to them of its own.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:02.46,1:13:05.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And when it's done its job, it shuts off.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:05.88,1:13:08.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The energy may flow into a person nearby
Dialogue: 0,1:13:08.88,1:13:11.93,Default,,0,0,0,,with some physical problem.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:12.03,1:13:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And you witness the miraculous,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:14.03,1:13:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,the person crippled and psychotic and delusional.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:17.44,1:13:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,After a few minutes, you hear them quiet down,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:19.44,1:13:21.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the delusions disappear,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:21.64,1:13:23.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and the crippled, supposedly crippled person
Dialogue: 0,1:13:23.64,1:13:25.53,Default,,0,0,0,,gets up and walks away.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:25.64,1:13:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And you go, oh, oh.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:27.80,1:13:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So the miraculous occurs.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:31.81,1:13:33.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It happens simultaneously of its own.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:33.81,1:13:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It has to do with the karmic ripeness of the person.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:37.81,1:13:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,One day we were in Korea.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:39.81,1:13:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,We were sitting across from lunch.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:42.81,1:13:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And this woman, and I'm not getting why,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:44.81,1:13:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,they placed her across from me.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:46.81,1:13:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,In the middle of it, all of a sudden,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:48.81,1:13:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,she's telling me how she's paralyzed on one side
Dialogue: 0,1:13:50.81,1:13:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and paralyzed on this side and another.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:52.81,1:13:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And we had similar experiences with others,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:54.81,1:13:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,nuns and people.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:56.81,1:13:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And, oh, I suddenly sort of got what she was looking for.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:58.81,1:14:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought, oh, God, she's looking for her healing.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:00.81,1:14:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that has nothing to do with me.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:02.72,1:14:04.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So I just thought lovingly of her
Dialogue: 0,1:14:05.00,1:14:08.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and, you know, what I could do on a limited basis.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:09.00,1:14:12.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And the energy then either brings about the miraculous
Dialogue: 0,1:14:13.00,1:14:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,or it does not.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:15.00,1:14:18.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It has nothing to do with you as a person, nothing at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:19.00,1:14:21.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It just uses you as an antenna
Dialogue: 0,1:14:22.00,1:14:24.89,Default,,0,0,0,,to radiate the energy elsewhere.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:25.00,1:14:26.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's that kundalini energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:27.00,1:14:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, you now have right brain dominance.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:30.97,1:14:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,This kundalini energy creates this etheric brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:34.97,1:14:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And the etheric brain is what accumulates
Dialogue: 0,1:14:37.97,1:14:40.86,Default,,0,0,0,,the karmic consequences of all your decisions.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:40.97,1:14:43.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The gift of divinity is free choice,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:43.28,1:14:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,that only you have the rudder to steer the ship.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:49.77,1:14:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And once you set your compass in a certain way,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:53.77,1:14:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,you bring certain energies and powers in to be supportive.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:57.77,1:15:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,One thing that happens then is right brain dominance.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:01.77,1:15:04.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It's nonlinear.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:04.22,1:15:06.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It releases endorphins.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:06.40,1:15:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You feel peace, positive emotions.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:09.40,1:15:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And the thymus gland is supported.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:12.40,1:15:15.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Increase of killer cells, increase of immunity,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:15.40,1:15:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,rapidity of healing.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:17.40,1:15:19.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of the healings that even in this lifetime
Dialogue: 0,1:15:19.40,1:15:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,were, you know, frankly, miraculous.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:22.40,1:15:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It balances the acupuncture system.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:26.47,1:15:30.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And you have a positive kinesiologic response.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:30.47,1:15:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The track to the emotions,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:32.67,1:15:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,then, is slower than that through the etheric cortex.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:40.89,1:15:43.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we instantly, like today's experience,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:44.02,1:15:45.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I looked at her, I got exactly where she's at.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:46.02,1:15:48.93,Default,,0,0,0,,She looked at us, got exactly where we're at.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:49.02,1:15:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Both of us knew there was nothing but peace on each side.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:52.18,1:15:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,We instantly knew it.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:54.80,1:15:56.69,Default,,0,0,0,,She didn't have to talk to us or convince us.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:56.80,1:15:59.69,Default,,0,0,0,,One glance, we all knew we were okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:59.80,1:16:01.69,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how long it took.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:01.80,1:16:03.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Because we got it right here.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:03.80,1:16:05.69,Default,,0,0,0,,We got what her energy was, what our energy was.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:05.89,1:16:08.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And it all went fine.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:08.80,1:16:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason I'm telling you this now
Dialogue: 0,1:16:10.82,1:16:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,is because it was stored in the hippocampus.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:13.82,1:16:15.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It was stored in the hippocampus
Dialogue: 0,1:16:15.82,1:16:17.72,Default,,0,0,0,,as a positive experience.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:17.82,1:16:19.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You see how a person who's paranoid
Dialogue: 0,1:16:19.82,1:16:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,would think she did it on purpose,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:21.82,1:16:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,insists he's going to sue her,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:23.82,1:16:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,claim he's got a whiplash.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:25.82,1:16:27.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You see how, what a different thing, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:27.82,1:16:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,A whole different energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:30.63,1:16:33.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, oh, oh, oh, oh.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:33.18,1:16:35.07,Default,,0,0,0,,There was one on TV, remember?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:35.18,1:16:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it was San Francisco or someplace.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:37.27,1:16:39.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And you see all the people coming out of the front of the bus,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:39.18,1:16:41.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and then you see all the street people
Dialogue: 0,1:16:41.18,1:16:43.07,Default,,0,0,0,,climbing in the back of the bus
Dialogue: 0,1:16:43.18,1:16:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,so that they can come out the front
Dialogue: 0,1:16:45.18,1:16:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and they take down their name and address.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:49.69,1:16:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It was hysterical. It was on television.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:51.85,1:16:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, God.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:53.85,1:16:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, we said, we don't need your insurance company.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:55.85,1:16:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't need our insurance company.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:57.85,1:16:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you know, we blessed each other.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:59.85,1:17:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And we were only concerned that the other one was upset.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:01.85,1:17:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I gave her a hug. She gave us a hug.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:03.85,1:17:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,We were only concerned that the other person
Dialogue: 0,1:17:05.85,1:17:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,might be upset by this.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:07.85,1:17:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I think that's normal, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:10.80,1:17:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,But other people are not that way.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:12.80,1:17:14.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Other people are not that way.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:14.80,1:17:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Other people would see it as an opportunity, you see.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:18.05,1:17:21.94,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so then the spiritual energy, over 200,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:22.05,1:17:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,transforms you as an individual,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:25.05,1:17:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,changes your brain physiology,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:27.05,1:17:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,changes how you experience life,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:29.05,1:17:32.05,Default,,0,0,0,,changes how people respond to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:32.14,1:17:35.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Over 200, New York gets to be a very friendly place.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:35.14,1:17:38.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody knocked their brains out.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:38.14,1:17:40.05,Default,,0,0,0,,They knocked their brains out to be nice to us.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:40.14,1:17:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what more you could expect.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:42.14,1:17:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, we stayed at a beautiful hotel.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:44.14,1:17:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Guest of a wonderful person.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:46.14,1:17:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Saw beautiful things.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:48.14,1:17:50.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Went for a ride in the park.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:50.14,1:17:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, what more do you want?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:52.14,1:17:54.65,Default,,0,0,0,,They even had a parade for us.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:54.76,1:17:56.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It was called Israeli Day Parade.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:56.76,1:17:58.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Right down Fifth Avenue.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:58.76,1:18:01.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Right down Fifth Avenue.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:01.48,1:18:03.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And that was interesting.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:04.00,1:18:05.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And police, I'd never seen police like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:06.00,1:18:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We looked out the hotel window.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:08.10,1:18:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,They had police from Fifth Avenue
Dialogue: 0,1:18:10.00,1:18:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,all the way down a couple of blocks,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:12.00,1:18:13.89,Default,,0,0,0,,running through into Central Park.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:14.00,1:18:15.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa, what a security operation.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:16.00,1:18:18.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:18.44,1:18:20.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, and it went peacefully.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:20.44,1:18:27.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing else happened.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:27.50,1:18:29.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of evolution, you see,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:29.50,1:18:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,over 200, the mind is different.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:31.63,1:18:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,People of more advanced consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:18:34.63,1:18:38.52,Default,,0,0,0,,assume everybody has a mind like yours.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:38.63,1:18:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact is, they do not.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:42.63,1:18:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,They do not have a mind like yours.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:45.63,1:18:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are there so many crazies in the world?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:47.63,1:18:50.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you live here and they live there.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:50.63,1:18:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's how 155 thinks as compared to 275.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:57.63,1:19:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you see, the lower mind is a different attractor field.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:03.78,1:19:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a different energy field.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:05.78,1:19:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,People that are into esoteric information,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:08.78,1:19:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,such as the Bailey books and all,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:10.78,1:19:12.97,Default,,0,0,0,,are familiar with all these terms
Dialogue: 0,1:19:13.07,1:19:15.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and the esoteric terminology.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:16.07,1:19:22.01,Default,,0,0,0,,But lower mind has a different centralized focus of energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:22.10,1:19:26.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It attracts to it then different what attracts to higher mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:26.10,1:19:30.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Higher mind has a different attractor field.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:30.10,1:19:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So we can talk about the physics of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:33.10,1:19:38.81,Default,,0,0,0,,On that plane, lower mind then sees things
Dialogue: 0,1:19:38.90,1:19:41.81,Default,,0,0,0,,in a pretty vicious kind of a paradigm.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:41.90,1:19:43.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You hear these politicians get on
Dialogue: 0,1:19:43.90,1:19:46.81,Default,,0,0,0,,with their veins standing out in their neck
Dialogue: 0,1:19:46.90,1:19:50.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and calling the other one a liar.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:50.35,1:19:52.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't matter which party they belong to.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:52.35,1:19:54.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just they've lost their marbles.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:54.35,1:19:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And they shout and scream and vilify.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:59.68,1:20:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And you wonder who are they talking to
Dialogue: 0,1:20:01.68,1:20:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,because they're certainly turning these people off.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:04.84,1:20:07.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Turning them off.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:07.25,1:20:09.14,Default,,0,0,0,,No, they're talking to these people.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:09.25,1:20:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, well, if you're talking to these people,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:12.25,1:20:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,now they make sense.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:14.69,1:20:18.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Now they make sense.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:18.17,1:20:22.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, obviously, they're appealing to these people here
Dialogue: 0,1:20:22.17,1:20:25.06,Default,,0,0,0,,because here you're talking from reason.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:25.17,1:20:30.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You're speaking rationally, calmly, with reason,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:30.17,1:20:33.06,Default,,0,0,0,,with proof, with ethics, morality.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:33.17,1:20:35.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You're talking to 275.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:35.73,1:20:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Over here, you're talking to 155.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:39.73,1:20:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow, what a big difference.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:41.73,1:20:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And the big difference is not only 100 points,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:44.73,1:20:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,but here you've crossed over 200
Dialogue: 0,1:20:46.64,1:20:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,to ethical responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:49.64,1:20:51.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you're under 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:51.64,1:20:54.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Two different categories of the citizenry.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:54.64,1:20:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And you will hear the politicians screaming
Dialogue: 0,1:20:57.64,1:21:00.27,Default,,0,0,0,,emotionally to these people here
Dialogue: 0,1:21:00.38,1:21:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,because that's what appeals to these people here.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:03.38,1:21:06.27,Default,,0,0,0,,These people here are turned off by it.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:06.38,1:21:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I hear politicians screaming, calling names, invective.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:10.40,1:21:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I see the veins in his neck standing out.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:13.40,1:21:15.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I've turned off on the guy already.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:15.40,1:21:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't care what he's talking about.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:17.51,1:21:20.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not the kind of animal I can listen to.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:20.40,1:21:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And I say, turn down the TV.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:22.40,1:21:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Good God, I'm trying to think.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:25.69,1:21:26.60,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:28.07,1:21:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Lower mind, then, is concerned with content.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:31.07,1:21:33.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Higher mind is concerned with context.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:34.17,1:21:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Context.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:35.17,1:21:37.06,Default,,0,0,0,,In what context?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:37.17,1:21:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,This one quotes what somebody said.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:39.17,1:21:42.06,Default,,0,0,0,,What they do is purposely misquote it out of context,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:42.17,1:21:44.06,Default,,0,0,0,,so as to make the person look negative.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:44.17,1:21:47.06,Default,,0,0,0,,This person says, yes, but under what context?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:47.17,1:21:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, when was it that happened?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:49.30,1:21:51.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, World War II was on.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:51.19,1:21:53.10,Default,,0,0,0,,That does change it quite a bit, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:53.19,1:21:55.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:55.19,1:21:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so this is concrete.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:57.39,1:21:59.30,Default,,0,0,0,,This is more abstract.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:59.39,1:22:01.30,Default,,0,0,0,,This is specific.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:01.39,1:22:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,This is more general.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:03.39,1:22:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,This gets very personalized.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:05.39,1:22:08.22,Default,,0,0,0,,This is more impersonal.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:08.31,1:22:10.22,Default,,0,0,0,,This looks at specifics.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:10.31,1:22:12.22,Default,,0,0,0,,This looks more at the class.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:12.31,1:22:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,This one is reactive.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:15.00,1:22:16.89,Default,,0,0,0,,This one is detached.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:17.00,1:22:20.02,Default,,0,0,0,,This one says, let's give him a good punch.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:20.02,1:22:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,This one says, let's think about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:22.02,1:22:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the best move?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:24.02,1:22:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the best move we could make under these circumstances?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:27.02,1:22:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,More detached and reflective.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:31.90,1:22:34.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The recall of events of these people at 155
Dialogue: 0,1:22:34.90,1:22:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,is different than the recall of events of people at 275.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:40.55,1:22:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:41.55,1:22:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,We were talking at lunch about, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:44.77,1:22:47.89,Default,,0,0,0,,the experience of being in the military in World War II.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:48.00,1:22:50.89,Default,,0,0,0,,People above this respect the honor
Dialogue: 0,1:22:50.89,1:22:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,of the former foe.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:53.89,1:22:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,People on this side still probably hate him.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:55.89,1:23:03.09,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so this is reactive and this is detached.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:03.18,1:23:08.97,Default,,0,0,0,,This one says, wait a second, let's think it over.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:09.07,1:23:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,This one plans for things,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:11.07,1:23:14.10,Default,,0,0,0,,but this one begins to, tries more to create it.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:14.19,1:23:16.10,Default,,0,0,0,,This one looks for definition.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:16.19,1:23:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,This one tries to get, yeah, but what is the meaning of it?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:20.72,1:23:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,But this is pedestrian.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:22.61,1:23:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,This is transcendent.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:25.28,1:23:29.18,Default,,0,0,0,,This is motivated, like by greed or anger or resentment.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:29.28,1:23:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,This deals more in inspiration.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:31.28,1:23:34.18,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the overall intention of the field?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:34.28,1:23:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,We're trying to build a company here.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:36.28,1:23:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:37.44,1:23:39.35,Default,,0,0,0,,We're trying to build a party.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:39.44,1:23:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,We're trying to create a new environment.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:44.97,1:23:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,This is involved with morals.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:46.97,1:23:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,This is involved with ethics.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:49.17,1:23:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,This is right and wrong.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:51.17,1:23:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Ethics is a little more sophisticated
Dialogue: 0,1:23:53.17,1:23:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,because ethics depends also on the situation.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:56.17,1:24:01.39,Default,,0,0,0,,What's ethical in one situation is unethical in another.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:01.48,1:24:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether the Patriot Act is passed during time of war
Dialogue: 0,1:24:05.52,1:24:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,or time of peace makes a big difference.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:07.52,1:24:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Time of peace, I'm going to get out there and parade.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:11.71,1:24:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Time of war, it's obviously a necessity.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:14.71,1:24:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Examples, principles.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:17.84,1:24:20.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Physical and emotional survival,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:20.31,1:24:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,this one is interested more in intellectual development.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:23.31,1:24:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,This one is interested in immediate pleasure
Dialogue: 0,1:24:26.92,1:24:28.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and gratification.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:28.92,1:24:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,This one is more interested in the fulfillment of the potential,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:31.92,1:24:34.81,Default,,0,0,0,,long-term goals over short-term goals.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:34.92,1:24:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,This one wants to acquire.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:37.02,1:24:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,This one wants to savor it.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:39.02,1:24:43.75,Default,,0,0,0,,This one wants to think and wants denotation.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:43.85,1:24:46.75,Default,,0,0,0,,This person wants to process it
Dialogue: 0,1:24:46.85,1:24:49.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and see what is the meaning of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:49.85,1:24:51.75,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the significance?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:51.85,1:24:53.75,Default,,0,0,0,,This one looks for significance.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:53.85,1:24:55.75,Default,,0,0,0,,This one looks for facts.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:56.14,1:24:58.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I can see the facts on television.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:58.14,1:25:00.03,Default,,0,0,0,,But what is the significance of that?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:00.14,1:25:03.03,Default,,0,0,0,,What does it mean for all of us, mankind?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:03.14,1:25:05.03,Default,,0,0,0,,What does it mean for Americans?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:05.14,1:25:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,What does it mean for world peace?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:07.14,1:25:09.03,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the meaning of that?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:09.14,1:25:12.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So this side is more like reflective
Dialogue: 0,1:25:12.14,1:25:14.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and lives more in the field.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:14.14,1:25:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a contemplative lifestyle.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:16.14,1:25:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Contemplative people are living more in the overall field.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:20.27,1:25:23.17,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the significance to all of us?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:23.27,1:25:26.46,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the impact going to be?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:26.46,1:25:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, outsourcing jobs, price of gasoline, etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:31.46,1:25:34.35,Default,,0,0,0,,This side just walks about the price of gasoline.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:34.46,1:25:36.35,Default,,0,0,0,,But this side is looking at, yeah,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:36.46,1:25:38.35,Default,,0,0,0,,what is the overall impact going to be
Dialogue: 0,1:25:38.46,1:25:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,on international monetary valuations, etc.?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:44.93,1:25:46.93,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the long-term,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:47.02,1:25:50.93,Default,,0,0,0,,what does it mean to all of us in humanity?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:51.02,1:25:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:57.82,1:26:01.81,Default,,0,0,0,,This brings us the rule,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:01.90,1:26:03.81,Default,,0,0,0,,the rule of Western society
Dialogue: 0,1:26:03.81,1:26:05.86,Default,,0,0,0,,in the time of the ancient Greeks
Dialogue: 0,1:26:05.97,1:26:11.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and is interpreted by Christianity, etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:11.97,1:26:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And as current in our daily experience of law
Dialogue: 0,1:26:15.97,1:26:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and construction of the United States government,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:19.97,1:26:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,comes out of this whole tradition.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:22.97,1:26:25.86,Default,,0,0,0,,This morning we quoted my favorites of childhood,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:25.97,1:26:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,of Aristotle and Socrates, etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:28.97,1:26:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,They calibrate, so we'll see.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:31.97,1:26:33.86,Default,,0,0,0,,These are the people
Dialogue: 0,1:26:33.86,1:26:36.77,Default,,0,0,0,,who influenced the whole intellectual development of man.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:36.86,1:26:40.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The United States Constitution calibrates at 710.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:41.02,1:26:42.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the highest in the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:43.02,1:26:44.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the highest it has ever been,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:45.02,1:26:47.82,Default,,0,0,0,,higher than any theocracy even.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:47.93,1:26:50.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So if we look at the great books of the Western world,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:50.93,1:26:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I had the good fortune to obtain a whole set.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:53.93,1:26:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It came out in the 50s.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:55.93,1:26:58.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It was put together by Mortimer Adler
Dialogue: 0,1:26:58.93,1:27:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,at the University of Chicago.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:00.93,1:27:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The scholars of the day.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:02.93,1:27:04.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And there was much argument.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:04.82,1:27:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,They studied this, chewed it over for years,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:07.82,1:27:11.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and came out with a list of the greatest minds
Dialogue: 0,1:27:11.82,1:27:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that have ever lived up until recent times,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:14.82,1:27:17.72,Default,,0,0,0,,up until the last one is Sigmund Freud.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:17.82,1:27:19.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So the last volume is Freud.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:19.82,1:27:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is Freud?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:22.07,1:27:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember Freud's at 499.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:24.07,1:27:26.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So the great books of the Western world,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:27.07,1:27:28.97,Default,,0,0,0,,the intellectual tradition
Dialogue: 0,1:27:29.07,1:27:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,out of which we all drew our education,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:31.07,1:27:32.97,Default,,0,0,0,,our law, our government,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:33.07,1:27:34.97,Default,,0,0,0,,all is the fallout
Dialogue: 0,1:27:35.07,1:27:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,of this.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:37.27,1:27:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,From 350 BC down to the present time,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:42.01,1:27:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,this is what has dominated rational, traditional society.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:46.01,1:27:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,This is traditional America that I grew up in.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:49.01,1:27:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Reason, intellect, ethics, morals, responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:54.01,1:27:57.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You see how Thomas Aquinas,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:57.10,1:27:59.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I studied Thomas Aquinas.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:59.10,1:28:01.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I went to a Jesuit college.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:01.27,1:28:04.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I went to a state teacher's college,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:04.27,1:28:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,then a Jesuit college.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:06.27,1:28:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Then the University Medical School.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:09.27,1:28:14.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The medical school reflected the impact
Dialogue: 0,1:28:15.03,1:28:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,because it was a Jesuit medical school.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:18.03,1:28:21.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The ethics of Thomas Aquinas
Dialogue: 0,1:28:22.03,1:28:23.93,Default,,0,0,0,,impacted us all.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:24.03,1:28:25.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So we grew up as physicians
Dialogue: 0,1:28:26.03,1:28:27.93,Default,,0,0,0,,who had an ethical, moral responsibility
Dialogue: 0,1:28:28.03,1:28:29.93,Default,,0,0,0,,to our patient.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:30.03,1:28:31.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Money and all that was secondary.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:32.03,1:28:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And if they didn't have the money,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:34.31,1:28:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,you told them to hell with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:36.96,1:28:38.85,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the way it was done
Dialogue: 0,1:28:38.96,1:28:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,because we had taken an oath.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:41.11,1:28:43.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So that was the impact then,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:43.11,1:28:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Thomas Aquinas.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:45.11,1:28:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And here we see Aristophanes and Aristotle
Dialogue: 0,1:28:49.43,1:28:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,at 498.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:51.43,1:28:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,498 is about as far as you can go.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:53.43,1:28:56.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It's about as far as you can go.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:56.43,1:28:58.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Socrates is not on here
Dialogue: 0,1:28:58.43,1:29:00.34,Default,,0,0,0,,because Socrates didn't write any books.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:00.43,1:29:02.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, he's in Plato.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:02.43,1:29:06.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So Socrates calibrates at 540.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:06.34,1:29:08.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Socrates impressed me
Dialogue: 0,1:29:08.34,1:29:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,because at a time,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:10.34,1:29:12.23,Default,,0,0,0,,see, this is 350 BC.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:12.34,1:29:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So he couldn't get the notion of God
Dialogue: 0,1:29:15.34,1:29:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,out of Christianity.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:16.34,1:29:18.27,Default,,0,0,0,,He wasn't born yet.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:18.36,1:29:20.27,Default,,0,0,0,,He was far away from the Orient.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:20.36,1:29:22.27,Default,,0,0,0,,He never heard of the Buddha.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:22.36,1:29:24.46,Default,,0,0,0,,He never heard of the Indian gurus
Dialogue: 0,1:29:24.56,1:29:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,that came out of India.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:27.68,1:29:32.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Without any monotheistic precedence then,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:32.68,1:29:36.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Socrates arrived at a profound commitment
Dialogue: 0,1:29:36.59,1:29:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,to truth as the pathway to God.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:39.59,1:29:41.81,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, Socrates,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:41.90,1:29:43.81,Default,,0,0,0,,when he was accused of corrupting the youth
Dialogue: 0,1:29:43.90,1:29:45.81,Default,,0,0,0,,by telling them the truth,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:45.90,1:29:48.81,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a dangerous occupation.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:48.90,1:29:50.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, God bless.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:50.90,1:29:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And by telling the truth,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:54.42,1:29:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Socrates then put himself
Dialogue: 0,1:29:56.42,1:29:58.31,Default,,0,0,0,,in bad favor with the government
Dialogue: 0,1:29:58.42,1:30:00.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and he was condemned to death.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:00.42,1:30:03.31,Default,,0,0,0,,However, Socrates was given a chance
Dialogue: 0,1:30:03.42,1:30:05.43,Default,,0,0,0,,to recant.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:05.53,1:30:08.43,Default,,0,0,0,,He had by court order
Dialogue: 0,1:30:08.43,1:30:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,to commit suicide by drinking the hemlock
Dialogue: 0,1:30:12.67,1:30:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,or he could recant.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:15.05,1:30:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,He felt it would negate the central meaning
Dialogue: 0,1:30:18.18,1:30:21.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and purpose and thrust of his entire life
Dialogue: 0,1:30:21.18,1:30:23.07,Default,,0,0,0,,to negate truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:23.18,1:30:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And so rather than violate truth,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:25.18,1:30:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,he drank the hemlock and died.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:28.18,1:30:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,540.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:30.18,1:30:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,What a profound belief.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:32.18,1:30:35.07,Default,,0,0,0,,What a profound investment
Dialogue: 0,1:30:35.18,1:30:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,at a time when religion was not even dominant,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:38.07,1:30:39.97,Default,,0,0,0,,except the old Greek gods
Dialogue: 0,1:30:40.07,1:30:41.97,Default,,0,0,0,,who don't carry much energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:42.07,1:30:44.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Aristotle.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:45.01,1:30:46.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We see Augustine at 503.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:47.01,1:30:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So these are almost all
Dialogue: 0,1:30:49.01,1:30:50.90,Default,,0,0,0,,in the high 400s
Dialogue: 0,1:30:51.01,1:30:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,with a few exceptions.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:53.01,1:30:55.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Augustine jumps over to 503.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:56.01,1:30:58.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the great names,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:58.39,1:31:00.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Copernicus, Dante at 505.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:00.39,1:31:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,He jumps over.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:02.39,1:31:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We see Darwin at 450.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:04.39,1:31:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Darwin at 450.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:06.68,1:31:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So the theories of evolution then
Dialogue: 0,1:31:09.57,1:31:11.47,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrate at 450.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:11.57,1:31:14.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Descartes, who we quoted quite a bit today,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:14.77,1:31:16.67,Default,,0,0,0,,at 470.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:16.77,1:31:18.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you see Engels somehow got
Dialogue: 0,1:31:18.77,1:31:20.67,Default,,0,0,0,,in the good guy list here.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:20.77,1:31:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,He snuck in back door at 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:22.77,1:31:25.02,Default,,0,0,0,,He's sort of iffy.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:25.11,1:31:26.02,Default,,0,0,0,,A little bit iffy.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:26.11,1:31:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You could push him over either way.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:29.39,1:31:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the great scientific geniuses of time.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:32.39,1:31:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Freud at 499.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:34.39,1:31:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I've told the story about Freud before.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:37.39,1:31:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Galen at 450.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:39.39,1:31:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,They're great physicians.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:41.39,1:31:43.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Galileo at 485.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:43.34,1:31:45.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, Galileo certainly upset the world
Dialogue: 0,1:31:45.34,1:31:47.23,Default,,0,0,0,,by telling the truth, didn't he?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:47.34,1:31:49.75,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, it was 400 years
Dialogue: 0,1:31:49.85,1:31:51.75,Default,,0,0,0,,before his excommunication was recalled.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:51.85,1:31:53.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You can call it exactly
Dialogue: 0,1:31:53.85,1:31:57.02,Default,,0,0,0,,swift and speedy justice,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:57.13,1:31:59.02,Default,,0,0,0,,but it did happen.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:59.13,1:32:01.02,Default,,0,0,0,,That's Galileo's karma, probably.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:01.13,1:32:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:03.89,1:32:06.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably Galileo's karma
Dialogue: 0,1:32:06.53,1:32:08.43,Default,,0,0,0,,or the field out of which he said it.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:08.53,1:32:10.43,Default,,0,0,0,,But you see,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:10.53,1:32:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,heresy is not that what you see
Dialogue: 0,1:32:12.43,1:32:15.34,Default,,0,0,0,,heresy is not that what you say
Dialogue: 0,1:32:15.43,1:32:17.34,Default,,0,0,0,,is a violation of the church belief.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:17.43,1:32:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,That is not the basis for heresy.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:19.43,1:32:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Heresy is when ordered by the church
Dialogue: 0,1:32:22.50,1:32:24.39,Default,,0,0,0,,to cease and desist
Dialogue: 0,1:32:24.50,1:32:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,or to decline what you've said you refused.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:27.68,1:32:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So heresy is
Dialogue: 0,1:32:29.68,1:32:32.59,Default,,0,0,0,,denial of the ecclesiastic
Dialogue: 0,1:32:32.68,1:32:34.59,Default,,0,0,0,,authority of the church.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:34.68,1:32:36.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not because you said
Dialogue: 0,1:32:37.07,1:32:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,that the earth goes around the sun
Dialogue: 0,1:32:39.56,1:32:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and vice versa.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:41.46,1:32:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because when ordered
Dialogue: 0,1:32:43.46,1:32:45.35,Default,,0,0,0,,by ecclesiastic authority
Dialogue: 0,1:32:45.46,1:32:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,to refute his theory,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:47.46,1:32:49.77,Default,,0,0,0,,he refused.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:49.86,1:32:51.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see, that is the basis of heresy
Dialogue: 0,1:32:51.86,1:32:53.77,Default,,0,0,0,,is refusal to bow to the authority
Dialogue: 0,1:32:53.86,1:32:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,of ecclesiastic
Dialogue: 0,1:32:56.42,1:32:58.89,Default,,0,0,0,,bodies,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:58.98,1:33:02.27,Default,,0,0,0,,the pope and the cardinals.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:02.36,1:33:04.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, Gaius at 465,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:04.36,1:33:06.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Harvey, you discovered
Dialogue: 0,1:33:06.36,1:33:08.27,Default,,0,0,0,,the circulation of the blood.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:08.36,1:33:10.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And you see Hegel,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:10.36,1:33:12.27,Default,,0,0,0,,who plays a great part in history
Dialogue: 0,1:33:12.36,1:33:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,in a sort of negative way.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:13.36,1:33:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,We were talking about him at lunch.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:15.36,1:33:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Hegel was the great leading philosopher
Dialogue: 0,1:33:17.36,1:33:19.27,Default,,0,0,0,,in the German philosophy
Dialogue: 0,1:33:19.36,1:33:21.32,Default,,0,0,0,,in the 1800s.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:21.43,1:33:23.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, we think this is all textbook stuff
Dialogue: 0,1:33:23.43,1:33:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,for kids,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:25.43,1:33:27.32,Default,,0,0,0,,but our daily life in great detail
Dialogue: 0,1:33:27.43,1:33:29.32,Default,,0,0,0,,is completely determined
Dialogue: 0,1:33:29.43,1:33:31.32,Default,,0,0,0,,by the output of these minds.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:31.43,1:33:35.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all the output of these minds.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:35.43,1:33:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So it is of great significance.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:37.43,1:33:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Hegel had one of Hegel's
Dialogue: 0,1:33:41.61,1:33:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,essential to his philosophy,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:43.61,1:33:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,was his teaching
Dialogue: 0,1:33:45.61,1:33:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,of the absolute.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:47.61,1:33:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Hegel said,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:49.81,1:33:51.72,Default,,0,0,0,,within creation there is that
Dialogue: 0,1:33:51.81,1:33:53.72,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the absolute,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:53.81,1:33:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,irrefutable, irreducible,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:57.80,1:33:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the absolute,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:59.85,1:34:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,by which everything else
Dialogue: 0,1:34:01.85,1:34:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,is measurable.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:03.89,1:34:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that's the core of what we do
Dialogue: 0,1:34:05.89,1:34:07.80,Default,,0,0,0,,with consciousness research.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:07.89,1:34:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The infinite field of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:34:09.89,1:34:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,itself is the absolute
Dialogue: 0,1:34:11.89,1:34:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,by which we compare everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:13.89,1:34:15.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So when I ask her by her arm
Dialogue: 0,1:34:15.80,1:34:17.69,Default,,0,0,0,,how many llamas,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:17.80,1:34:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm saying numerically
Dialogue: 0,1:34:19.80,1:34:23.17,Default,,0,0,0,,as compared to the absolute.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:23.27,1:34:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The calibrated levels of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:34:25.27,1:34:27.17,Default,,0,0,0,,are relative to the absolute,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:27.27,1:34:30.85,Default,,0,0,0,,which is infinite.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:31.18,1:34:33.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Within our domain,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:33.18,1:34:35.09,Default,,0,0,0,,the highest level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:34:35.18,1:34:37.09,Default,,0,0,0,,historically has been at 1000.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:37.18,1:34:39.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So we can compare it
Dialogue: 0,1:34:39.18,1:34:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,with the highest it's ever been
Dialogue: 0,1:34:41.18,1:34:43.09,Default,,0,0,0,,or we can compare it with the absolute.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:43.18,1:34:45.09,Default,,0,0,0,,In calibrating levels of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:34:45.18,1:34:47.81,Default,,0,0,0,,we compare it with the absolute.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:47.92,1:34:49.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So Hegel's theory was correct.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:49.81,1:34:51.72,Default,,0,0,0,,If you calibrate it,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:51.81,1:34:53.72,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll see that he was correct.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:53.81,1:34:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,However, Karl Marx was a young
Dialogue: 0,1:34:55.81,1:34:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,revolutionary and Karl Marx
Dialogue: 0,1:34:57.81,1:34:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,had an unresolved edible complex.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:59.81,1:35:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Apparently,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:03.46,1:35:05.35,Default,,0,0,0,,unresolved relationship with his father
Dialogue: 0,1:35:05.46,1:35:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,because the father figure Hegel
Dialogue: 0,1:35:07.46,1:35:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of saying,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:09.46,1:35:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,wow, what a brilliant mind,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:11.46,1:35:13.35,Default,,0,0,0,,he decided to refute Hegel.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:13.46,1:35:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And Marx came up with the theory.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:15.46,1:35:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You see all these people
Dialogue: 0,1:35:17.46,1:35:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,are in the 400s or even up to the 500s.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:19.46,1:35:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And you see Marx
Dialogue: 0,1:35:21.35,1:35:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,bizarrely is at 130.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:23.35,1:35:25.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You wonder how did he get in this?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:25.35,1:35:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Marx then defied the absolute
Dialogue: 0,1:35:31.18,1:35:33.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and defied Father Hegel
Dialogue: 0,1:35:33.18,1:35:35.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and hatched an adolescent theory
Dialogue: 0,1:35:35.18,1:35:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,based on the perpetrator-victim model,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:37.18,1:35:39.07,Default,,0,0,0,,a dualistic model.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:39.18,1:35:41.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the absolute is a monism,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:41.18,1:35:43.07,Default,,0,0,0,,is a oneness.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:43.18,1:35:45.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The perpetrator-victim model
Dialogue: 0,1:35:46.07,1:35:47.97,Default,,0,0,0,,is a dualistic split.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:48.07,1:35:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything Marx looked at then
Dialogue: 0,1:35:50.39,1:35:52.30,Default,,0,0,0,,looked like perpetrator-victim.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:52.39,1:35:54.35,Default,,0,0,0,,If you look at employment,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:54.35,1:35:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,employee, job,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:56.35,1:35:58.26,Default,,0,0,0,,perpetrator-victim.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:58.35,1:36:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,If you look at people in bank,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:00.35,1:36:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,perpetrator-victim.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:02.35,1:36:04.26,Default,,0,0,0,,If you look at businessmen,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:04.35,1:36:06.26,Default,,0,0,0,,capitalist, peasant.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:06.35,1:36:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So he split everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:08.35,1:36:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So he didn't see that when
Dialogue: 0,1:36:11.10,1:36:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,a company moves to town
Dialogue: 0,1:36:13.10,1:36:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that it's mutually,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:15.10,1:36:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,he doesn't see mutuality at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:17.10,1:36:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,How can the company survive
Dialogue: 0,1:36:19.10,1:36:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and make money without the workers?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:21.10,1:36:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:23.00,1:36:24.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It was Thiensville, Wisconsin.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:25.00,1:36:26.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The only thing that made a living there
Dialogue: 0,1:36:27.00,1:36:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,was the cannery.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:29.43,1:36:31.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Without the cannery,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:31.43,1:36:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,how would these people pay
Dialogue: 0,1:36:33.43,1:36:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,for new harnesses for their horses,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:35.43,1:36:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,get a new tractor?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:37.69,1:36:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,On the other hand,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:39.69,1:36:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the cannery couldn't work
Dialogue: 0,1:36:41.85,1:36:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,without the workers.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:43.85,1:36:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,See, and I was a worker there.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:46.14,1:36:48.81,Default,,0,0,0,,We got an extra five cents
Dialogue: 0,1:36:48.92,1:36:50.81,Default,,0,0,0,,for everything over 12 hours.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:50.92,1:36:52.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And a red hot pea cannery,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:52.92,1:36:54.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I tell you.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:54.81,1:36:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,We had another big track going over.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:56.81,1:36:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It was horrendous, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:58.81,1:37:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,working on these hot warehouses.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:00.81,1:37:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,They had no windows, no fans.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:02.85,1:37:04.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It was 125, 130,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:04.85,1:37:07.26,Default,,0,0,0,,lifting these heavy boxes.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:07.35,1:37:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And so which is the perpetrator
Dialogue: 0,1:37:09.35,1:37:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and which is the victim, eh?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:11.35,1:37:16.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, if all the workers quit,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:16.23,1:37:18.14,Default,,0,0,0,,the business would collapse.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:18.23,1:37:20.14,Default,,0,0,0,,If the business moved out of town,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:20.23,1:37:22.14,Default,,0,0,0,,the town would go into abject poverty.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:22.23,1:37:24.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So what he didn't get is mutuality.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:24.23,1:37:26.14,Default,,0,0,0,,He didn't get mutuality.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:26.23,1:37:28.14,Default,,0,0,0,,That men and women serve each other.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:28.23,1:37:30.14,Default,,0,0,0,,He didn't get the unity
Dialogue: 0,1:37:30.23,1:37:32.14,Default,,0,0,0,,that the worker and the employer
Dialogue: 0,1:37:32.23,1:37:34.14,Default,,0,0,0,,serve each other.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:34.23,1:37:36.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The student and the teacher serve each other.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:36.23,1:37:38.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, he didn't get the oneness of it all.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:38.52,1:37:40.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Which costs 100 million people
Dialogue: 0,1:37:40.52,1:37:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,their lives in this lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:43.26,1:37:45.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Because when that's projected
Dialogue: 0,1:37:45.26,1:37:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and politicized,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:47.39,1:37:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,then it becomes a sort of revolutionary.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:49.39,1:37:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you see the history of Russia,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:51.39,1:37:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the history of France,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:53.39,1:37:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the history of communist China,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:55.39,1:37:57.31,Default,,0,0,0,,all those things.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:57.42,1:37:59.31,Default,,0,0,0,,When applied to the real world,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:59.42,1:38:01.31,Default,,0,0,0,,the current of the way Marx saw,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:01.42,1:38:03.31,Default,,0,0,0,,projected on the world,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:03.42,1:38:05.47,Default,,0,0,0,,is not the way the real world is at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:05.57,1:38:08.47,Default,,0,0,0,,When projected onto the economy of China,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:08.57,1:38:12.47,Default,,0,0,0,,30 million people starved to death in China
Dialogue: 0,1:38:12.57,1:38:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,as a consequence of Marxism.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:14.57,1:38:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Marxist collectivism.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:17.38,1:38:19.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody works on a collectivist farm, man.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:19.38,1:38:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You only work on a farm
Dialogue: 0,1:38:21.38,1:38:25.53,Default,,0,0,0,,if you pocket the money from the watermelons.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:25.64,1:38:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, you're supposed to be just a good guy,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:28.89,1:38:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:31.02,1:38:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,parading around for some slogan.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:33.02,1:38:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, your energy goes down
Dialogue: 0,1:38:35.02,1:38:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,at the end of the day.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:37.18,1:38:40.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And 30 million people starved to death
Dialogue: 0,1:38:40.18,1:38:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,as a consequence of Marxism.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:42.18,1:38:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So when people try to resell it
Dialogue: 0,1:38:45.18,1:38:47.07,Default,,0,0,0,,in new clothes in today's society,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:47.18,1:38:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I turn a deaf ears.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:49.18,1:38:51.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been tried already.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:51.18,1:38:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So that is Hegel and Hume,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:55.39,1:38:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,all these Kant, of course,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:57.39,1:39:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,the Kantian categories of logic and reason,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:00.39,1:39:01.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Locke.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:01.30,1:39:05.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So Marx at 130 then has had a profound.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:05.26,1:39:08.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So what is the point of this?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:08.31,1:39:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The point of this is that fallacy then,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:11.31,1:39:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,fallacy is the source of war
Dialogue: 0,1:39:13.31,1:39:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and truth is the foundation of peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:17.31,1:39:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,That a calibrated level of 130
Dialogue: 0,1:39:20.47,1:39:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,can take down an entire empire.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:23.47,1:39:25.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You get enough people.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:25.64,1:39:27.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what memes are, M-E-M-E-S.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:27.64,1:39:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You get that to be a common saying
Dialogue: 0,1:39:30.34,1:39:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,that everybody begins to adopt as though it's truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:33.34,1:39:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, the working man, drop your chains.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:36.38,1:39:38.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You have nothing but freedom.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:38.38,1:39:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Working men, drop your chains.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:40.40,1:39:42.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, first of all, he wasn't in any chains.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:42.40,1:39:45.31,Default,,0,0,0,,He wasn't in any chains.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:45.40,1:39:47.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Unite.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:47.40,1:39:49.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You have nothing but your chains to lose.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:49.40,1:39:51.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Cost then 100 million people.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:51.65,1:39:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Not to mention what happened after,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:53.65,1:39:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Stalin did after World War II.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:56.65,1:39:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Stalin sent another 30 million
Dialogue: 0,1:39:58.65,1:40:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,off to the gulags to die of various ways.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:02.56,1:40:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So we can't exactly close our eyes
Dialogue: 0,1:40:08.52,1:40:10.42,Default,,0,0,0,,to the hermeneutics
Dialogue: 0,1:40:10.52,1:40:16.18,Default,,0,0,0,,of distorted relativistic epistemology.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:16.27,1:40:20.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You heard it here.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:20.72,1:40:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The downside of the distortions of logic
Dialogue: 0,1:40:25.81,1:40:29.64,Default,,0,0,0,,by trying to twist the meaning.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:29.75,1:40:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It means what I want it to mean.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:31.75,1:40:33.64,Default,,0,0,0,,That denies the absolute.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:33.75,1:40:36.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, in the Bill of Rights
Dialogue: 0,1:40:36.93,1:40:38.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and the Constitution of the United States,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:38.97,1:40:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,we're guaranteed freedom of speech.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:42.80,1:40:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,What is speech?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:45.63,1:40:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Speech comes out of here.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:47.63,1:40:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Does it come out of here?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:49.63,1:40:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Does it come out of here?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:52.75,1:40:54.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Does it mean action?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:55.03,1:40:57.93,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so if you say speech means expression,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:58.03,1:40:59.93,Default,,0,0,0,,everything is expression,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:00.03,1:41:02.93,Default,,0,0,0,,including bombing busloads of children.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:03.03,1:41:04.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Ku Klux Klan, that's expression.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:05.03,1:41:08.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything's expression, is it not?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:08.22,1:41:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see the downside
Dialogue: 0,1:41:11.11,1:41:13.02,Default,,0,0,0,,of distorting meaning, then.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:14.34,1:41:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The absolute meaning of a meaning
Dialogue: 0,1:41:16.34,1:41:19.23,Default,,0,0,0,,is the very strength of law.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:19.34,1:41:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,When you begin to change the meaning of the word,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:22.34,1:41:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,you've now lost the reliability
Dialogue: 0,1:41:24.34,1:41:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and the strength of law.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:26.34,1:41:28.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Law can no longer save you.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:28.94,1:41:31.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You know that law can no longer protect you.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:31.94,1:41:34.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You think it can?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:35.03,1:41:37.93,Default,,0,0,0,,By relativistic epistemology,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:38.03,1:41:40.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I can make anything sound like anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:41.03,1:41:44.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So, and the courts are no longer ruled
Dialogue: 0,1:41:44.02,1:41:47.18,Default,,0,0,0,,by law,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:47.27,1:41:49.81,Default,,0,0,0,,then anything can go.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:49.92,1:41:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, the loudest voice
Dialogue: 0,1:41:51.92,1:41:55.73,Default,,0,0,0,,will be the one that carries the vote.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:55.84,1:41:57.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Here we're talking about content.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:57.84,1:42:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,We said the naive person thinks only of content,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:00.97,1:42:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,ignores the context.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:04.02,1:42:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You can make this wrong
Dialogue: 0,1:42:06.02,1:42:07.93,Default,,0,0,0,,so long as you ignore the context.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:08.02,1:42:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the proximate field,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:10.26,1:42:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,the proximate field.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:12.26,1:42:14.15,Default,,0,0,0,,That could be the economic conditions
Dialogue: 0,1:42:14.26,1:42:16.31,Default,,0,0,0,,at the time,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:16.31,1:42:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,let's say the relationship of men and women,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:18.31,1:42:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,in which men dominated,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:20.60,1:42:22.50,Default,,0,0,0,,it appeared to society,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:22.60,1:42:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,to feminists that way,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:24.64,1:42:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,not to men or to the women they were with
Dialogue: 0,1:42:26.64,1:42:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,because they had equality.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:29.34,1:42:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,America was agrarian.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:31.34,1:42:33.50,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was born,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:33.60,1:42:36.50,Default,,0,0,0,,50% of America was agrarian, rural.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:36.60,1:42:38.61,Default,,0,0,0,,In the rural world,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:38.72,1:42:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,being a mesomorph,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:40.72,1:42:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,having muscles and testosterone
Dialogue: 0,1:42:42.72,1:42:44.61,Default,,0,0,0,,is what you need.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:44.72,1:42:46.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The woman works like a dog inside
Dialogue: 0,1:42:46.61,1:42:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,five kids and diapers and God knows what all.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:49.75,1:42:51.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Equal and, you know, equal.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:51.75,1:42:55.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The woman was revered, revered.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:55.35,1:42:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,We stood up when mother entered.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:57.35,1:42:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,We did not use vile language.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:59.35,1:43:01.26,Default,,0,0,0,,We did not use vulgar language.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:01.35,1:43:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,In my home, you could not even say
Dialogue: 0,1:43:03.35,1:43:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,pew or stink.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:07.63,1:43:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom, I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:11.59,1:43:15.57,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so it was equality.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:15.68,1:43:17.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You can distort it and now project it
Dialogue: 0,1:43:17.68,1:43:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,into today's society,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:19.57,1:43:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and you can see how you can do a make wrong
Dialogue: 0,1:43:22.77,1:43:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,by projecting it backwards in time.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:25.77,1:43:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,That's called a shift of context.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:27.77,1:43:30.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Is slavery wrong?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:30.35,1:43:32.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It is in today's world.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:32.35,1:43:36.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Was slavery wrong throughout the history of mankind?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:36.35,1:43:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:38.35,1:43:40.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody practiced slavery
Dialogue: 0,1:43:40.35,1:43:43.25,Default,,0,0,0,,because it was a part of the cultural evolution
Dialogue: 0,1:43:43.35,1:43:46.25,Default,,0,0,0,,of all societies 100%.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:46.35,1:43:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,In the days of ancient Rome,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:49.78,1:43:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the slaves outnumbered
Dialogue: 0,1:43:51.78,1:43:55.03,Default,,0,0,0,,the free men by ten to one.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:55.14,1:43:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Ten to one.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:57.72,1:43:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And slaves were the architects.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:59.72,1:44:01.61,Default,,0,0,0,,They were the learned people of the day,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:01.72,1:44:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,but legally they were slaves, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:04.84,1:44:06.73,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so you go backward in time,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:06.84,1:44:08.73,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll find that slavery only got,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:08.84,1:44:11.97,Default,,0,0,0,,came to a legal end, I think, in 1961
Dialogue: 0,1:44:12.06,1:44:15.97,Default,,0,0,0,,as a result of JFK's pressure on that company,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:16.06,1:44:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,country, 1961.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:18.15,1:44:21.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So it was, to say, is slavery wrong?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:21.15,1:44:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,In this world, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:23.15,1:44:26.06,Default,,0,0,0,,In the past world, it's the way it was for everyone.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:26.15,1:44:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:28.15,1:44:30.06,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, slavery was an advancement.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:30.15,1:44:34.76,Default,,0,0,0,,In the early, more primitive barbaric days,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:34.85,1:44:36.76,Default,,0,0,0,,when you invaded a country like the Vikings,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:36.85,1:44:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,you slaughtered everybody.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:39.63,1:44:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The Vikings got smart.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:41.63,1:44:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,They found if you don't slaughter them,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:43.63,1:44:45.56,Default,,0,0,0,,you can sell them.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:45.65,1:44:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of bloody death,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:47.65,1:44:49.85,Default,,0,0,0,,you now had a chance at least to live, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:49.94,1:44:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so it was discovered in Africa,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:51.94,1:44:53.85,Default,,0,0,0,,it was discovered in Scandinavia.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:53.94,1:44:55.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The Vikings, all of them had slaves,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:55.85,1:44:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and slavery was a way of life.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:57.85,1:45:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It was where society was at that point in its evolution.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:02.85,1:45:04.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can see how making it wrong
Dialogue: 0,1:45:04.85,1:45:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,by projecting it backward in history.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:06.85,1:45:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Was it wrong at the time of the Vikings?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:09.85,1:45:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course not. Of course not.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:13.38,1:45:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The turn-of-the-century opium
Dialogue: 0,1:45:18.10,1:45:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,was the content of many patent medicines.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:22.10,1:45:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It was discovered that a lot of,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:25.85,1:45:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,especially farm ladies,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:27.85,1:45:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,got very dependent on this patent medicine.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:29.85,1:45:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,To feel good,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:32.07,1:45:33.97,Default,,0,0,0,,they just had to have a swig
Dialogue: 0,1:45:34.07,1:45:35.97,Default,,0,0,0,,a couple of times a day.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:36.07,1:45:37.97,Default,,0,0,0,,90% alcohol, the rest tincture of opium,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:38.07,1:45:40.05,Default,,0,0,0,,or the rest opium, rather.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:40.14,1:45:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,They were slightly stoned.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:42.14,1:45:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,They were feeling good,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:44.14,1:45:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and boy, this medicine works.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:46.14,1:45:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course it worked.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:48.14,1:45:50.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You felt rotten,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:50.14,1:45:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,you had some of this Pinkham's egg elixir,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:52.14,1:45:54.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and you felt good.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:54.14,1:45:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So what's wrong with that?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:58.31,1:46:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,How come Harry Anslinger took a negative view of that?
Dialogue: 0,1:46:02.31,1:46:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it was found out
Dialogue: 0,1:46:04.22,1:46:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,that it was addicting.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:06.42,1:46:08.31,Default,,0,0,0,,We didn't know it was addicting
Dialogue: 0,1:46:08.42,1:46:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,for a generation or two.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:11.34,1:46:13.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, retrospectively,
Dialogue: 0,1:46:13.34,1:46:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,you say, well, they were wrong.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:17.61,1:46:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,But that's retrospective.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:19.61,1:46:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,At the time, people didn't understand
Dialogue: 0,1:46:21.61,1:46:23.57,Default,,0,0,0,,that that was addictive.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:23.68,1:46:26.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Laudanum, people didn't understand
Dialogue: 0,1:46:26.96,1:46:28.85,Default,,0,0,0,,that cocaine was addictive.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:28.96,1:46:30.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Sigmund Freud got addicted to it.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:30.96,1:46:33.72,Default,,0,0,0,,People didn't know those were addictive.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:33.81,1:46:35.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see,
Dialogue: 0,1:46:35.81,1:46:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,falsification by projection
Dialogue: 0,1:46:37.81,1:46:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,elsewhere in history
Dialogue: 0,1:46:39.72,1:46:41.81,Default,,0,0,0,,is today's fallacy.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:41.92,1:46:43.81,Default,,0,0,0,,This is true
Dialogue: 0,1:46:43.92,1:46:45.81,Default,,0,0,0,,only within this context here.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:45.92,1:46:47.85,Default,,0,0,0,,To sell medicine
Dialogue: 0,1:46:47.94,1:46:49.85,Default,,0,0,0,,that contains opium
Dialogue: 0,1:46:49.94,1:46:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,in today's world
Dialogue: 0,1:46:51.94,1:46:53.85,Default,,0,0,0,,would certainly be non-integrous.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:53.94,1:46:55.85,Default,,0,0,0,,In the world of the 1890s,
Dialogue: 0,1:46:55.94,1:46:57.85,Default,,0,0,0,,it was honesty.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:57.94,1:46:59.85,Default,,0,0,0,,When he said, drink this, you'll feel better,
Dialogue: 0,1:46:59.94,1:47:01.85,Default,,0,0,0,,that's the truth. You did.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:01.94,1:47:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Smoke this little thing
Dialogue: 0,1:47:04.97,1:47:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and you'll feel better. Whatever.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:07.39,1:47:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:09.47,1:47:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's the context.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:11.38,1:47:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, you cannot tell truth
Dialogue: 0,1:47:13.38,1:47:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,without the context.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:15.38,1:47:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And what makes any of it work
Dialogue: 0,1:47:17.38,1:47:19.27,Default,,0,0,0,,is the ultimate non-linear infinite context,
Dialogue: 0,1:47:19.38,1:47:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and that is the energy field
Dialogue: 0,1:47:21.38,1:47:23.27,Default,,0,0,0,,of consciousness itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:23.38,1:47:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Within the infinite energy field,
Dialogue: 0,1:47:25.38,1:47:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,the absolute,
Dialogue: 0,1:47:27.38,1:47:29.27,Default,,0,0,0,,is the relative local conditions
Dialogue: 0,1:47:29.38,1:47:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,whose meaning and significance
Dialogue: 0,1:47:32.81,1:47:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,you cannot understand
Dialogue: 0,1:47:34.81,1:47:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,unless you state the context.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:36.81,1:47:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Consequently, man is never known.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:38.81,1:47:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,We saw the greatest thinkers
Dialogue: 0,1:47:40.81,1:47:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,of all time.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:42.88,1:47:44.77,Default,,0,0,0,,They arrived at what is truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:44.88,1:47:46.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The greatest minds that have ever lived
Dialogue: 0,1:47:46.88,1:47:48.85,Default,,0,0,0,,could not define truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:48.94,1:47:50.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And the simple thing that was missing
Dialogue: 0,1:47:50.94,1:47:52.93,Default,,0,0,0,,is this here. Truth is only true
Dialogue: 0,1:47:53.03,1:47:54.93,Default,,0,0,0,,within a specified context.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:55.03,1:47:56.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And even that is not true
Dialogue: 0,1:47:57.03,1:47:58.93,Default,,0,0,0,,unless compared
Dialogue: 0,1:47:59.03,1:48:00.93,Default,,0,0,0,,with the absolute.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:01.03,1:48:02.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, calibrating levels of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,1:48:03.03,1:48:04.93,Default,,0,0,0,,as far as I can discern
Dialogue: 0,1:48:05.03,1:48:06.93,Default,,0,0,0,,from a study of everything
Dialogue: 0,1:48:07.03,1:48:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,like forever,
Dialogue: 0,1:48:09.43,1:48:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,is the first thing
Dialogue: 0,1:48:11.43,1:48:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that has included
Dialogue: 0,1:48:13.32,1:48:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the necessary ingredients
Dialogue: 0,1:48:15.32,1:48:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,to arrive at a science of truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:17.32,1:48:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,A science of truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:19.32,1:48:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what time we break for lunch,
Dialogue: 0,1:48:21.32,1:48:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,or afternoon, what?
Dialogue: 0,1:48:23.32,1:48:26.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Three o'clock, okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:26.15,1:48:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so you may think this is irrelevant,
Dialogue: 0,1:48:28.15,1:48:30.06,Default,,0,0,0,,but having heard it, you'll realize
Dialogue: 0,1:48:30.15,1:48:32.06,Default,,0,0,0,,because it'll come to you
Dialogue: 0,1:48:32.15,1:48:34.06,Default,,0,0,0,,all of a sudden with annoyingness,
Dialogue: 0,1:48:34.15,1:48:36.43,Default,,0,0,0,,oh, I get what that means.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:36.53,1:48:38.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I get what that means.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:38.53,1:48:40.43,Default,,0,0,0,,This is something we did when we were in Europe.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:40.53,1:48:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,We spoke at some place or other.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:42.82,1:48:44.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is the Louvre.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:44.82,1:48:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The Louvre calibrates,
Dialogue: 0,1:48:46.82,1:48:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget what, 500 or 700,
Dialogue: 0,1:48:48.82,1:48:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,500, oh yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:50.82,1:48:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, the Louvre calibrates,
Dialogue: 0,1:48:52.82,1:48:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, the Louvre,
Dialogue: 0,1:48:54.82,1:48:56.76,Default,,0,0,0,,it took centuries to build it.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:56.85,1:48:58.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The monarchs, that was the castle,
Dialogue: 0,1:48:58.85,1:49:00.76,Default,,0,0,0,,that was the palace
Dialogue: 0,1:49:00.85,1:49:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,for the monarchs,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:02.85,1:49:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,for several monarchs.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:04.85,1:49:06.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a stunning experience.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:06.85,1:49:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the things that sort of knocks you out
Dialogue: 0,1:49:08.85,1:49:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,is you can wander in and around
Dialogue: 0,1:49:10.85,1:49:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and look at the most famous valuable paintings
Dialogue: 0,1:49:12.85,1:49:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,in the whole world and take photographs of them,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:14.85,1:49:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,right?
Dialogue: 0,1:49:16.85,1:49:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Imagine that.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:18.85,1:49:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Taking photographs of all these things,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:20.85,1:49:23.23,Default,,0,0,0,,no charge,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:23.34,1:49:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,just take as many pictures as you want.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:25.47,1:49:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The Mona Lisa does have a glass panel in front of her,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:29.47,1:49:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,but other than that,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:31.47,1:49:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the rest of them seem to be relatively exposed.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:33.47,1:49:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,They do have a guard in each room.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:35.85,1:49:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Having remembered what happened to the Pieta,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:37.85,1:49:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I always thought it's rather
Dialogue: 0,1:49:39.85,1:49:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,either foolhardy or courageous of them
Dialogue: 0,1:49:41.85,1:49:43.75,Default,,0,0,0,,to allow this.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:43.85,1:49:45.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You remember what happened to the Pieta
Dialogue: 0,1:49:45.75,1:49:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,when a psychotic person attacked it,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:47.75,1:49:51.93,Default,,0,0,0,,because the core of the ego hates God,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:52.03,1:49:53.93,Default,,0,0,0,,is always atheistic,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:54.03,1:49:55.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and all of the relativistic philosophies
Dialogue: 0,1:49:56.03,1:49:57.93,Default,,0,0,0,,which are currently causing
Dialogue: 0,1:49:58.03,1:49:59.93,Default,,0,0,0,,so much contention in America
Dialogue: 0,1:50:00.03,1:50:01.93,Default,,0,0,0,,are all atheistic.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:02.03,1:50:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,All. 100%.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:04.64,1:50:07.31,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:07.42,1:50:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's the usefulness and practicality
Dialogue: 0,1:50:09.42,1:50:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,in today's world.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:11.42,1:50:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So the book I'm just finishing has to do
Dialogue: 0,1:50:13.42,1:50:15.31,Default,,0,0,0,,with what is truth, defining it,
Dialogue: 0,1:50:15.42,1:50:17.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and how does it affect
Dialogue: 0,1:50:17.43,1:50:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,the minds that appear throughout history
Dialogue: 0,1:50:19.43,1:50:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and throughout society,
Dialogue: 0,1:50:21.43,1:50:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout the greatest minds that have ever lived.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:23.43,1:50:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,We calibrated all the most famous names in history.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:26.43,1:50:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Charlemagne, whatever.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:28.43,1:50:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,How does it reflect itself in writers,
Dialogue: 0,1:50:30.43,1:50:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,in movies, in TV,
Dialogue: 0,1:50:32.43,1:50:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,in all the expressions of our current society?
Dialogue: 0,1:50:35.43,1:50:39.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So here's a relativistic scale
Dialogue: 0,1:50:39.43,1:50:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,of great usefulness in many dimensions.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:43.47,1:50:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,This is just the scale
Dialogue: 0,1:50:45.38,1:50:47.27,Default,,0,0,0,,for practicality up to 600.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:47.38,1:50:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,This side is called us.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:49.38,1:50:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,This side is called them.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:51.47,1:50:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,This can be our company.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:53.47,1:50:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,This can be our target market.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:55.47,1:51:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,This can be our club, garden club.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:00.47,1:51:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,This can be their community.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:02.47,1:51:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You can line it however you want.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:04.50,1:51:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, we'll go to the next one.
